column6: First Botany Cosmeceuticals Rejuvenating Rose Water Toner 4 fl. oz. Spray
column13: I've used different brands of rose water before and loved the results
column14:
This toner smells lovely, just as I would expect from rose water. I've used different brands of rose water before and loved the results. So, I was exited to try the First Botany brand.
The toner uses some great natural ingredients like rose oil and aloe vera juice. These are mild ingredients that are recommended for people with sensitive skin.
However, it also uses Phenoxyethanol and Tetrasodium EDTA which are a stabilizer and preservative respectively. Both of these ingredients are penetration enhancers, meaning that they break down your skin's natural barriers, so that these ingredients go right into your bloodstream. Tetrasodium EDTA is also made from formaldehyde and sodium cyanide which are known carcinogens.
Since I received this item as a review, I did not have a chance to go over the ingredient listing in detail. Had I known this, there is a good chance that I would have skipped reviewing this product.
I received this product at a discount in exchange for my unbiased review. All thoughts and opinions contained herein are my own.

column6: Anti Age Synergy Essential Oil Blend. 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade.
column13: First PT product I didn't like. It's the aroma.
column14: I started my EO journey a little over 3 months ago. After attending a disappointing presentation by a rep from an mlm company. It spurred me on to do my own research. I came across Plant Therapy (PT) and choose it as my go to company for essential oils. I made this choice because they espouse safe usage (have hired one of the go to people on using EOs safety as a consultant who also developed their "kids safe" line), have trained aromatherapists on staff to answer questions, support a fabulous FB page on safe usage, etc. PT really thinks of the little touches, the EO bottles have labels on the top with the names of the oils/synergies. Trust me, it really makes it easier to find what you want/need as your collection grows. You don't have to pick up each oil and read the name. You can just glance from above. On top of that, they always offer free shipping!  This is the first time I've gotten a roller ball from PT. It was offered at a reduced price for an honest review, so I thought it would be a good time to try one. Price wise, I'm not sure why people buy the pre-diluted rollerballs. I'm sure it must be for the convenience. While all of the kidsafe rollerballs have the dilution %, I couldn't find this for the adult rollerballs. All of the rollerballs use fractionated coconut oil as their carrier oil. The pluses are that it's inexpensive and it has a lot longer shelf life then most carrier oils. The minus is that it doesn't have the therapeutic benefits of the other carrier oils (including regular coconut oil.) If you buy the undiluted synergy, you can make many rollerballs for a fraction of the price of one prediluted rollerball.  I am not one who loves floral scents. The Anti-Age Synergy has some over powering florals in it--Geranium, Jasmine, Rose (and non floral Sandalwood, which I don't like) predominate, but I could be wrong. I used it on my face a few hours before I took my Pilates class this morning. Despite the fact that it seemed to absorb easily, it's all I could smell HOURS later. It was still VERY strong. When mixing EOs for therapeutic purposes, you're not going for aroma, as you do when diffusing for non therapeutic reasons.  I think it's the kind of scent that's a love/hate smell. Just don't know if I can continue using it on my face. . I may try to use it on my hands (something further from my body) to see if I can stand it--and if it makes them look younger.  One last comment, the rollerball is a really nice one. Amber colored with a stainless steel rollerball. It's a higher quality rollerball then some that I've bought. The glass is thicker and shouldn't break easily. It should last a long time. In the past, I've had problems with plastic rollerballs falling out of the plastic holder when using fractionated coconut oil.  I can reuse this one for other products, although I may have to replace the rollerball parts if I can't get the scent out of the plastic part.

column6: Best Anti Aging Face Cream With Both Retinol and Hyaluronic Acid! LARGE Size Facial Moisturizer For Youthful Radiant Skin | Enriched with Green Tea, Vitamin E & B5
column13: The best bang for your buck!
column14:
I love trying new beauty products and creams so I was very excited to be offered this cream at a promotional price to review honestly. I have used it for a few weeks now and it's honestly not my personal favorite cream.

Things I don't like about it:
* It's heavy feeling. I feel it when I use it. It's a thick cream and for this reason I only use it at night. I can feel it on my face for a long time. Maybe that's a positive for it moisturizing longer?
* It's basically odorless, but there is a faint smell that is likely the retinol that I'm not fond of. I like the retinol so I can definitely deal with this.

Things I really like:
* The volume. Typically creams with these ingredients come in oversized bottles with 1 oz. or less. This one has 2 oz! I really like that.
* The pump locks. I love that the pump for the cream locks. I have hear that you should always keep any product with retinol tightly sealed to keep it working properly and this product does that.
* Overlooking the heaviness of the cream I can feel my skin tightening. I like that in an anti-aging cream! It feels like it's doing it's job.

Overall:
I like the product and will finish using the entire bottle. Will I order it again? I am still undecided.

column6: Cetaphil Gentle Skin Cleanser
column14:
I first purchased this Cetaphil (cleanser) two years ago when they were on sale at BJâ€™s. Now I buy them through my husbandâ€™s prime account which is cheaper. My husband tried this and loved it, now he uses this after he shaves his face, because he loves how smooth it make his face. This product has actually become a staple for me (and now my husband) which is hard to believe, because I LOVE trying new products. First, I want to point out that Cetaphil makes two cleanser this one and another, which is for â€œ Normal to oily skinâ€. I have never tried the other cleanser so I will not be doing a comparison in that perspective. What I will do is better help you understand what you will and will not get form this product.

What to expect: This product is very mild as it is for sensitive skin. You can use it with or without water. This product is very thin so I prefer using it without water, since using it with water (on a damp face) makes it feel like it is sliding off my face. This is a soap-free cleanser so do not expect suds when lathering with it. A little goes a long way for me a 16 oz bottle last three months; my routine is to use it morning and night. This specific product can be used on your body and on babies as well since it is non-comedogenic (it does not clog your pores which is how pimples are formed) and fragrance free. Your face will feel very soft and hydrated after using it. If you are currently experiencing an acne break out this product will not aggravate your skin, it will gently clean the pores which will overtime get rid of the acne.

What not to expect: This brand of Cetaphil will not fix acne breakout within a week, in fact it takes weeks from my experience, which is why I use another product when I have a break out. This product will not do anything for acne scaring or discoloration on your skin from my experience. After using this product your skin will not feel tight or dry.

Tips:
1) It cleans makeup brushes very well .
2) For acne prone people (like myself) you may need another product specifically for acne. Since this brand is for sensitive skin you can follow up with Cetaphil before or after using an acne specific product one that contains benzoyl peroxide or salicylic acid for spot treatment.

** Thanks for reading and I hope this information was helpful to you **eup brushes very well .

column14: This supplement (palm fruit extract) is well worth the money. I have only been taking it for a couple months now and my hair and skin are looking extra healthy. I live in California where its sunny everyday in the summer and my skin would usually burn after an hour or two of sun without sunscreen. I had read some reviews about its protective qualities within the skin, so I decided I would try for myself to see if it had affected my resistance to sunburn. I had my shirt off while I was outside gardening from noon until 7 pm. I thought for sure when I walked inside and showered I would feel the burn, but amazingly enough, I didn't burn! I haven't had this type of resistance to the sun since I was a child of about 10 years old vacationing in Florida without sunscreen. I'm not sure if everyone will experience this type of reaction, but it really makes me wonder how else this amazing fruit is benefiting my body in ways I cannot see!

column14:
This is labeled an anti-aging cream, but it doesn't have the ingredients like retinol that are normally associated with wrinkle removal. Instead I think the benefit is that it is a really nice moisturizer.

This goes on feeling very heavy and I initially worried that it would be greasy on my face for a long time. But it absorbed in quickly and left my face feeling soft but not greasy. I think it would be good for dry skin. This is the kind of moisturizer you might want to start before wrinkles are an issue, just to keep you skin in good condition. But because Sun is a big part of aging, be aware there is no SPF so you'll need some Sun protection.

column6: SilcSkin Anti-Wrinkle Pads
column13: I used it for several weeks and the lines are pretty much gone
column14: I bought this as a lark, I never imagined that it would actually be effective! I started noticing lines on my décolletage that I knew was from age, but I was surprised since I've been using sunblock for 30 plus years, I don't sunbathe or expose my skin to the sun without sunblock, so why was I getting these lines? I use skin creams religiously too, and nothing was making a difference in these lines. I put this on one night and by the morning my lines were barely visible! I couldn't believe it! I used it for several weeks and the lines are pretty much gone. The cons: the adhesion wears away quickly, it had not been a full month before the edges were rolling up; I like to apply moisturize on my chest at night and cannot apply any lotion before putting this on; I occasionally sleep on my side and I could not while wearing this thing. I only bought one, and haven't gotten another yet, but I'm sure once I see the lines return I'll be re-purchasing.

column6: Remington D3190A Damage Control Ceramic Hair Dryer, Ionic Dryer, Hair Dryer, Purple
column13: Great working hair dryer at an economical price
column14:
This is a great hair dryer at a fantastic price. It contains all the elements I have in my older and much more expensive hair dryer. It uses ionic ceramic toumaline to help reduce frizz and static that occurs from blow drying your hair. It has three heat settings and two blower speeds. I generally use the medium heat and the high blower, but I like to have the option to do a quicker dry with high heat when needed. It also includes the cool shot button which allows you to quickly cool the dryer down in the midst of drying and styling.

It has an easily removable filter, which is a huge plus. I once ruined a dryer because I didn't realize I needed to clean the filter. Now I periodically take the filter off and blow the "wrong way" through it to clear dust that accumulates through time. I do this about one a week or so and it helps keep the dryer running well and from burning out. I have placed a towel hook next to my bathroom sink and I hang the dryer on it. It keeps it off the counter, saving room and keeping it within easy reach.

The dryer comes with both a concentrator for when you are styling your hair or trying to focus the drying effort as well as a diffuser. The latter is important for me as my hair has a lot of wave and curl and blow drying it without the diffuser turns it all to frizz instead of curls.

I'm very pleased with this dryer and recommend it as a good and fairly inexpensive choice.

column6: Braun Silk Epil Female Epilator Se7921spa 1 Count
column13: Really like it - no more stubble, razor burn, or nicks
column14:
Bottom line: This thing is great. It is a bit uncomfortable to use the first time, but it gets easier. If you can get a tattoo, you can easily use this thing.
What I'm glad it has: The exfoliation brush is really useful. It keeps me from getting ingrown hairs and makes my legs even smoother.
What I wish it had: It would be nice if there was a suction cup holder for the shower. If I use it in the shower, I have to turn off the water in order to put it on the floor outside the shower without flooding my bathroom.

I spent about two weeks researching epilators and reading hundreds of reviews and finally decided on the Braun Silk-epil 9. It has a big head, different attachments that are useful, and can be used wet or dry. I noticed that a lot of reviewers got it free, so I went to the BzzAgent site they reference, took some surveys, and thanks to my good karma, they sent me one to try out! Score! As soon as I got it, I scanned the instructions and held my breath as I held it up to my shin. I was worried it was going to be really painful, but it was just like a rubber band snap. It was a little uncomfortable, but not bad. As I got closer to my ankles, it hurt a little bit, but nothing too bad.

So, after successful use on my legs, I got cocky and decided to do my upper lip. I put on the other cap and brought it up to my upper lip. Oh mother of pearl! I couldn't do it. I've never waxed my lip and wasn't prepared for it. Not sure if you remember the first time you plucked your eyebrows, but it was a similar sensation. My eyes watered and I couldn't go through with it. I went online and did some research and saw that some people used lidocaine cream to numb the area. I tried that on my upper lip and bikini line and didn't feel a thing. I've been using the exfoliating brush and haven't had any ingrown hairs. I've use the epilator a few more times since and it's really not been bad at all.

One word of caution: Ifyou have bug bites on your legs, be careful. I didn't realize that this little hair puller could also cut skin if it's swollen from a bug bite. That's why I gave it four stars instead of five.

Overall, I'm really happy with this epilator. I was completely prepared to buy it and, had I bought it instead of being awarded it, would have kept it. I have no desire to go back to shaving, razor burn, and nicks on my legs!

As anyone who has read my reviews knows, I am a natural health consultant and I use essential oils in many of my health related applications. In the past few days though my husband had a horrible toe infection and there was no way we could get in to see a doctor since most were booked solid.

column6: Razorock Mudder Focker Shave Soap
column14:
Wet shaving is an affordable luxury, and the possession of Razorock Mudder Focker shaving soap epitomizes an investment in an indulgence.
The fragrances are exotic yet familiar, with notes of sandalwood and strong bases of masculinity. A hot omega 48 brush, tapped slightly dry, with less than a teaspoon of this rich soap yielded the best lather I have ever had with a minimum of effort. Even after first pass, enough stayed on my face for some quick touch ups. I was able to use the remaining lather in my mug for a second application, and decided to go for an atg shave, with great results. I'm often a victim of razor burn and in growns, however, after a splash of witch hazel and a cold towel, and I found myself without either.
I would highly recommend this product.

column6: Lord FRESH Premium Safety Razor Merkur Style Head Model L125
column13: A very capable cheap Merkur copy from Egypt
column14:
Looks and shaves very much like my $40 Merkur razor, an obvious copy of what is likely to be the most popular modern razor head (the Merkur safety bar razor head, available with many handle options). The workmanship and handle material is not even close quality wise, yet it shaves side by side with the original. I bought it to give to my step father in law who loves to experiment with his shaves; but, won't spend anything on it. His 40 cent disposables will have to step aside for this and a blade assortment I also have for him. He loves the brush I got him and the soaps and creams I have sampled to him. He has even noted the location of a high end shave shop near his location.

It is a midrange razor on aggressiveness. Perhaps a bit to the mild side of the midpoint. It is positioned to be usable for most shavers. Very mild and very aggressive razors are suitable for much smaller groups as too many shavers object to their lack of ability to get the stubble (too mild) or because they too easily cut and scuff the face (too aggressive).

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14: This is the first time I have used a whitening product as I have always been concerned about damage to my teeth, caused by the whitening ingredients. My teeth are fairly white teeth but they could definitely be whiter. When I was offered a free sample of the product from Crest, I decided it was time to do a bit of research. I read other reviews and asked around if anyone had used a Crest whitening product. Most everything I heard was positive, so I agreed to try out the free sample. I am so glad I did. When I first received the product I read the instructions and the warning printed on the package to watch out for irritation and discomfort from using the product. I did experience some minor discomfort in my gums about a week in. However, I took a few days off from this toothpaste and when returning to it, the discomfort was gone. I have used the Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing System now for about a month. My teeth are definitely whiter and the toothpaste alone is a great product. My teeth feel clean all day long and the whitener has turned my pretty smile into a fabulous smile. #GotItFree

column6: DR. SCHOLLS ONE STEP CORN REMOVER 1045 1 EACH
column13: It worked for me -My corn was from wearing ill-fitting shoes-
column14:
Not all corn removers are created equal. This one worked for me. There are several versions of this product. The one I purchased was from Walmart. I was going to purchase if from Amazon but I was reading some of the reviews and was not sure if this was the product for me. When I went to Wally World to do my weekly shopping, I notice that the item was on rollback and had a coupon attached. The item I purchased was in a blue and white box and next to it was this box (red and yellow). I can only assume that the product has had a face-lift because the UPC on both boxes were the same but the blue and white box had the coupon affixed to it (so I took advantage of the coupon and rollback price. The exp date was good until 2016-sold). Moving on -the UPC: 10450 is in the right-hand corner of the box. The UPC on the back of the box is: 11017-104-50...Folks... This item worked for me. My corn was from wearing ill-fitting shoes. My footwear was too loose, and my foot would repeatedly slide and rub against the inside of shoe and the seam or stitch inside the shoe (New Balance). The pain was awful. I tried Mosco One Step Corn Remover Pads - They did not work for me. I thought I would just have to live with the pain. I used 2 of the bandages and in no time it just popped off. There are not instructions so here is how I used it. After shower...I applied the bandage- carefully open the package along the top seam to keep from ripping the bandage itself (tip from the hubby). Pull the full bandage out then remove the clear backing slowly...to avoid pulling the medicated center piece off.
This is not like a band-aid (the backing is a strip of plastic) and the bandage will not be flat.. the dark center piece must stay attached ..that is where the medicine is.. the white cushion around the dark center must also stay affixed as you pull the backing from the bandage. Place the bandage over the affected area. Allow the dark spot to lay on the actual corn and the whitecushion will cover the skin around the corn... then lay the side strips down and you are ready to go. Depending on how bad the corn is determines how many times you will need to repeat the process. The bandage is very, very strong. I was hard to get off even after a shower to change it out. After the second bandage...my corn just popped right off.
Hope this helps someone. Oh and my total cost was --ready???? $2.00 due to rollback and coupon....Happy dance!!!

column13: Extremely satisfied, very high quality and crisp freshness
column14:
I purchased this product amongst a few options for peppermint oil and have to say, I am sold! Don't get anything else, this is the real deal.
I used a 4 fl oz bottle in a 32 oz spray bottle (mixed with water). Water and this oil won't mix but shake your bottle and the mixture becomes milky and ready to be used - I spray around the house for a fresh scent and an immediate insect repellent. I used to have flies coming in the house. God knows why as my house is hyper-clean and from where they come (vent? chimney?) but I had one or two a day, enough to bug me (punt intended) making me jump to the spray chemicals. Since I stated to spray peppermint (and no more than once or twice a week), they don't come anymore. And yes, they do seem to also repel spider as advertised as I did not spot a "corner" web for a while.
Next usage is a few drop in a fresh glass of water. The provided glass dropper is perfect to make the measure - what a refreshing drink with immediate soothing effects! I am thrilled with the taste and freshness but also the effect as your body absorbs it - after a heavy meal or on boated days, it helps for real and you feel relaxed and calm.This brand is simply fantastic. I will buy it again I am sure (and so sold in this that I am now likely to try their other products)

column13: Works great, quality ingredients, does burn a bit if you get it in your rye.
column14:
Packaged in a 4 ML pump bottle. Using the pump is a bit tricky as the first time or two you use it, the pump is stiff and it "splashes" everywhere, while trying to just get a couple drops on the palm of your hand. I wish I could see a list of all ingredients and the label is smeared quite a bit and a few letters even missing. Here it is the best I can read it.

Purified water, soy and rice peptides, hyaluronic acid, Halxylz, roobos tea, Tripeptide-5, vegetable glycerin, sunflower oil, emulsi (can't read last part of word), macadamia oil, rose hip oil, vit E, Vit A, phenoxyethanol, and fragrance.

I really like the feel and softness of my eye area after using this. It has really helped the texture of my skin and the bags under them. I feel a very slight firming when it is drying. You want to use just one little pump which is very little, it goes a long ways, It is an off white in color, no real smell I can detect. I think the fine lines are a bit better also, but things won't happen over night I know.

I do wish it was a bigger bottle and had a dropper instead of a spray. It also does burn if you do get it in your eye by accident. I washed it out and it didn't burn long, but for something I am going to put that close to my eye, I wish it wouldn't burn. Those are the only reasons I took off a star.

column6: Rosemary Peppermint Body Butter
column13: Not a Blue Ribbon Showing for this Carolina Product.
column14: This item appears great on the photo and has a convincing description, but this seems to be a mom and pop concoction that is frankly not ready for the main stage with the established body butters/lotions.  First, the scents are weak and do not seem to mesh like other lotions using the same scents.  Rosemary and peppermint should get my nose as soon as I open the jar, but also not leave me gagging like some athletic cream.  The application is a greasy enough to pass as lotion, and maybe to grease a hog at the county fair, but I do not think it is fair to promote this product for much more than that.  I imagine a light and lingering smell for a reasonable period of time, but this is simply Crisco at the disco.  One last thing, the product should match the product label and advertisement because the Amazon.com listing states Rosemary Peppermint Body Butter, however the package says Rosemary Peppermint Foot Rub  8 oz.  The labels themselves are printed from a home computer and applied via a piece of tape, which is frankly not professional for an item that is sold for the human body. column6: Shea Moisture Olive & Green Tea Body Wash, 13 Ounce
column14: I first came across this product in Walgreens. Over the years my skin had become sensitive to all paraben based body soaps and washes. I broke out in hives using dove. So I knew after that that my skin had become super sensitive. I was raised to use organically whenever I could and Shea moisture just happened to be next to the Castile soap my grandmother had raised me on (which I'm also very allergic to) and after reading the ingredients I decided to get it and try it. First time it did leave my skin a tiny bit irritated but I added a few drops of lavender essential oil to the whole bottle and it cured all the itchies. Now I use it without the lavender oil and the greatest part about using organic, is that u can use it as a shampoo also. Or a shaving creme. It's multi purpose and a little bit (like dime size) to cover ur whole body in a nice lather and another dime for hair (mine was shoulder length when I started) and in 3 months my hair grew five inches. It protects hair from breakage and leaves it light and unburdened and clean. I even used it on my dog and it's safe for hypoallergenic pooches. Just doesn't kill fleas and stuff. As soon as I can find something that kills fleas ticks and eggs harshly yet is completely safe for my dog I plan on adding it to my favorite product. My dog deserves the best most organic stuff as much as I do. 5 stars all the way.

column13: Good for others. Not for me
column14:
I did not like this product at all.

Pros:
-Moisturizing. My skin did feel really soft each time I removed it.
-Non-irritating ingredients.
-Decent price.

Cons:
-Sunscreen ingredients sit on the skin. I could never get them to fully absorb into the skin. It just leaves a mask on my skin.
-Hard to rub in. First it seems watery out of the tub. I could never rub it in without it being streaky. It also dried quickly, which meant that the streaky look stayed on my skin. If I tried rubbing more, it would pill and fall off. All that rubbing hurt my sensitive cheeks.
-The white cast. I wore this the morning I got it. People asked me why I had cold cream on my skin.
-It cracked after drying. Even if I ended up without the uneven coverage and covered the whiteness with foundation, it would crack and rub off throughout the day.

This was such a disappointment. I thought the good reviews meant it would be perfect for me. Three days was all I could put up with this. This experience shows that just because something works for others does not mean it will work for you.

column6: Yes To Grapefruit Correct & Repair Rejuvenating Facial Wipes, 30 Count
column13: Quick, easy cleaning - but not as good as washing your face
column14: These face wipes are a quick and easy way to clean your face, although they are not as effective as washing your face. (I tested this by first using the face wipe, then toner on a cotton round, and there was still a bit of makeup left, as shown on the cotton.) Because of this, I do not use these daily, just when the convenience makes it worthwhile. These wipes did effective remove eye makeup and did not irritate my eyes, although I was very careful when using them around my eyes (and the package advises to avoid contact with eyes). The wipes have a pleasant enough smell, but I was a little disappointed because the Yes to Grapefruit scrub smells much better -- more fresh citrus scent. These Yes to Grapefruit wipes worked well for my combination skin, leaving it feeling soft and not sticky, as other versions of face wipes have done. By the way, these wipes also work well for a quick clean-up for the body and are refreshing, when showering isn't possible. The wipes stay moist for at least a couple of months in the packaging, as long as you carefully close the inner tab to seal it shut. They are made in Germany.  The Yes to Cucumber wipes have a nice cucumber scent and the Yes to Coconut wipes have a delicious, tropical coconut scent; I prefer these scents to the Yes to Grapefruit wipes. For better cleansing with a wipe than these "Yes to" variations, Blum's exfoliating wipes work well, because they have small beads that help clean (and also a great orange scent).

column6: Dermalogica Daily Resurfacer
column14: I bought this a while ago and didn't think that I saw any results on my aging skin. I do like Dermalogica as a brand, it is a minimalist brand dedicated solely to skin improvement, no splashy packaging or scents. I used the entire supply. I thought there was no noticeable difference or improvement, so I decided not to re-purchase. After a couple of weeks I noticed that my skin was more dull,  less hydrated and definitely less lustrous. I had not noticed the gradual improvement until I stopped using it. I re-purchased and included it in my skin care regimen, every other night, and my skin looks great. This is not an overnight miracle, but if you're middle aged and fighting gravity and the inevitable dull complexion, this is the way. If you need a miracle you should see a dermatologist. If you're fighting the good fight, using age smart products, and religiously applying sun block, you need to continue regular mild exfoliation and hydration. When I apply this, then apply nightly moisturizer, my skin remains well-hydrated through the night. This product has earned it's space on my shelf! Love it!

column6: SKG Handheld Nano Ionic Cool Mist Face Hydration Sprayer - Portable Facial Moisture Instrument
column13: Unusual, elegant aid to skin hydration and keeping cool. Easy to set up and use
column14:
The SKG Facial Spray is a really clever and efficient little gadget. I review beauty products across quite a few websites and I can honestly say I have never come across anything like this electrically powered facial spray before.
'Steamer' is slightly misleading as it implies a heat-produced vapour; what this device does is dispense an ultra fine mist of water droplets - it's almost steam-like but it is water, rather than water vapour.
It arrived beautifully packaged in a silk lined presentation box.
The unit uses a rechargeable battery which charges via a mini USB to USB charger - so a USB charging point is needed to use this, either a computer or a mains USB charger. I left the unit to charge overnight and it was ready for use in the morning.
The unit is filled with water by sliding off a panel on the back, taking out a silicone plug and using the pipette supplied (or a mini funnel if you have one). Refitting the silicone plug was a little tricky, but not too fiddly.

The unit is operated by simply sliding the front panel covering the spray downwards. It sprays instantly and continuously. The spray is very fine, but also very cooling - great to set makeup, or just to cool down.

It's virtually noiseless in use, which is a big plus - you won't be annoying fellow passengers on public transport for example. It's very elegant in presentation and will look great in the bathroom or dressing table.
I received a sample to review without cost, this is my honest and unbiased opinion.

column6: Waterpik Aquarius Water Flosser
column13: Easy to handle & does the job.
column14:
Does everything it's advertised to do. 10 levels of intensity of pulsing water stream to choose from. You're also able to choose between gum massage or water flossing with the push of a button. I see some people reviewing say it's difficult to remove the tip. Well, if you slide the side button up, the tip pops off instantly and easily. To re-attach, just slip it into the handle until it snaps in place. Doesn't get much easier than that. I also read where the wand button is "difficult" to move. When the unit is in the "off" mode, the button slides easily. When you turn it on, it's a tiny bit difficult because of the built up water pressure............but I didn't find it all that bad at all and don't understand what all the fuss is about. I slid the handle button on and off with minimal thumb pressure at setting 1 then dialed it up to 10. Once the water was gone, I was able to retract the handle thumb button easily. Comes with a total of 7 attachments but no "case" to store them in. I did find that Amazon carries the " Waterpik Convenient Hygienic Sturdy Storage Case for Replacement Tips , 6 Count". It's a tip storage case that comes with 6 tips--- 2 classic jets, 2 plaque seekers and 2 Orthodontic tips all for around 15 bucks. They also sell just the case without any replacement tips for around 9 bucks. The tips that come with this Storage case do fit the WP600, as well as several other units Waterpik sells. For a full list of compatible units, go online to Waterpik for a complete list.
I highly recommend using warm water so it's not as big shock to your teeth, especially if you've got tooth sensitivity issues.

column6: BMC Cute Colorful 90pc Sheer Mesh Reusable Expandable Slip On Make Up Brush Sleeve Protectors Set
column13: Cost Effective Alternative to The Brush Guard.
column14: I originally bought "[[ASIN:B0049J7P3S The Brush Guard Variety Pack]]" and started using for travel, so they got dirty.  I went to buy it again and found a more cost effective product!  Namely the "BMC Cute Colorful 90pc Sheer Mesh Reusable Expandable Slip On Make Up Brush Guard Protectors Set"  I was entranced by the colors, I won't lie.  But I found this to be a much better solution than the Brush Guard (sorry) and I probably will be using these for a long time.  Now it's not as sturdy as The Brush Guard, but it does the same exact thing, which is help me protect my brushes after washing and keep them upside down.  I find at the end it tapers off small which helps shape the brush.  It's a little weaker since you only see one plastic thread instead of 3 strands like The Brush Guard (when you expand it)...but it does the trick and perhaps helps air it out more since it's less covered in plastic.  (For those that don't understand what I mean, I'm trying to describe the "weave" which is stronger and more reinforced with The Brush Guard).  Technically speaking I do prefer The Brush Guard to this product, but not enough to pay more!  For those that have never tried The Brush Guard, disregard what I'm saying and just buy this product.  It comes with 90pcs, much more than you will need.  So I gave some to my sister.  Also what I didn't realize at first, is you can wash these if you use for travel and they get junky.  So get these now, you won't go wrong!

column14: Some foot cremes are very liquid, but this has a consistency similar to vaseline. It is not easily absorbed by the skin. Even hours later you still have a greasy layer on your skin. It's best to use it before you go to bed or you will smear it all over the carpet. But that's also not a good idea because it stains your linen permanently. Yet, we still like it. It's good for your feet and the smell is rather pleasant. It's not as good as Gehwol, but it's also cheaper.

column6: EcoTools Touch Up Set of 4 brushes
column14:
I made the mistake of purchasing a makeup brush set from amazon that had good description and reviews at a great price. Unfortunately the set was utter garbage and fell apart almost immediately.

After doing extensive research and watching Youtube recommends from beauty expert Lisa Eldridge, I bought this set, along with [[ASIN:B004Q1GCFG Sigma Beauty Basic Eyes Kit - 7 ct]] and https://smile.amazon.com/gp/product/B003UH0528/ref=oh_aui_detailpage_o07_s02?ie=UTF8&psc=1 to create a customized brush collection.

The Touch Up Set is of excellent quality and arrived exactly as the image and description indicates. I've used every brush multiple times and find the handles to be a great size, even though they are market as "travel". My favorite brush in the set is the white tipped brush - I use it for bronzer and it blends perfectly. I love EcoTools and have many other products in their line, I especially love their commitment to the a better planet.

From the first use, I was impressed with the Secret Outlast Completely Clean Clear Gel deoderant. It went on clear and I didn't worry about streaks on my black shirt. Putting it on, it did feel a little different than the solid that I normally use...it was more wet (for lack of a better term), but it dried very quickly and I didn't feel like I was wearing anything.

It wasn't until I got in my car to head home that I remembered the new deoderant that I had put on that day. Of course I did what any normal person would do...I sniffed my armpit. I was amazed that the deoderant had held up all day. The Secret Outlast Completely Clean Clear Gel doesn't have a strong sent, but it smells clean...I could still smell that clean scent at the end of the day. It definitely holds up!

Received the Braun Silk-épil 9 for free for testing purposes (but my opinion is my own) and so far it has not disappointed! After charging for an hour I turned it on and first tried the body exfoliating brush in the shower with some body gel. This was amazing! I felt like I was giving a soothing massage and it left my skin feeling soft. Next I went to epilate my legs and my bikini areas. For reference, I usually shave my legs, but wax my bikini area. I have used an epilator previously maybe 10 years ago but it left much to be desired so I switched to other methods. This particular epilator worked fantastic! I am obsessed. My bikini area which I was myself regularly using wax strips was used to hair removal, so it didn't hurt too much if any at all, and I was able to use it both wet and dry. I think dry worked better and it was quick without any need for precision. I pretty much kept running it back and forth until all the sensations of hair being zapped out were gone and everything was baby smooth. The light comes in handy for this, especially if using a magnifying mirror or using in the shower, probably my favorite feature. My legs aren't used to being removed in this fashion so that did hurt a bit more, went back and forth three times like a razor and everything was removed rather quickly to my surprise. It did leave some red bumps so I smoothed on some soothing lotion afterwards and it calmed down by dinner time. I would imagine the more I use this the less irritating it would get as my bikini zone did not get red. I absolute love using this for miscellaneous areas I would have otherwise tweezed a well such as my stomach, toes, etc.
Pros:
- Comes with two other attachments and for precision and a body exfoliating brush which all fits in a white waterproof drawstring bag. There is also a brush provided for cleaning as well.
- Leaves skin baby soft after using and for longer than shaving.
- Quick hair removal suitable for every day use.
- Charges quickly and can be used for up to 40 minutes.
- Can be used dry or wet for in the shower.
- Light feature comes very much in handy.
- Beautiful design and white pearly color.
Cons:
- Need to do it several times or so for the skin to get used to epilation.
- Takes an hour to charge, cannot be used with the cord.

column13: Great product. Simple ingredients that you can feel confident are sustainable and GMO / Pesticide Free.  Recommended.
column14:
This product is NOT just for manly beards, it does double duty for skin and feminine locks as well.

What You Get: (1) Beard Oil / Conditioner, (1.7 fl. oz. / 50mL) in MIRON glass bottle with black bulb glass dropper pipette.

Ingredients: USDA certified 100% Organic Argan Oil and 100% Organic Jojoba Oil.

PROs:

âž” I loved how this oil made my hair feel. I have long (down to my butt), natural barrel sized curls, which have a tendency to frizz out and go EWOK status (Star Wars reference). This oil left my hair soft, shiny and didn't weigh my curls down. Argan oil is also great for your cuticles - so if you work with your hands (as I do) this will help repair your skin as well. I liked that they didn't spoil the integrity of the oils by adding some kind of fragrance.

âž” Organic Jojoba Oil (Simmondsia chinensis). Pressed from plant seeds native to the American Southwest, the beans of a shrub like plant, and it is actually a liquid plant wax. USDA-certified Organic Jojoba Oil is a natural, time-honored moisturizer for skin and hair. Suitable for even the most sensitive skin, it penetrates quickly after application, and also makes for an enriching aftershave moisturizer. Moisturizes skin without leaving any oily residue â€¢ Effectively cleanses clogged pores â€¢ Helps prevent flakiness when massaged on scalp. Because Jojoba is not an oil but rather a wax, its shelf life and stability is considerably higher than most oils and rancidity is very rarely a concern.

Note: Jojoba oil may become cloudy and solidify as the temperature drops. This is a normal process that occurs from the hardening of the fats and waxes, and it will become stable at or around room temperature.

âž” Organic Argan Oil (Argania spinosa). In 1998, the Argan forest in Morocco was designated a UNESCO protected biosphere so argan oil is sustainable. Incredibly rich in Vitamin E, Essential Fatty Acids, and Proteins, Argan Oil helps fight lines, repair imperfections, minimize scars; all while restoring texture, elasticity and tone in skin. These clever little patches would have changed my life if they had been available years ago when my face was plagued by intermittent stress-related breakouts. Nowadays my skin rarely breaks out but, when it does, I now have the answer. These small, round patches are nearly invisible once on my face and work like a charm.

Using them is simple: wash the affected area, pat dry with a clean towel and apply the Dream Dot, pressing well for a few seconds. Ideally, the patch should stay in place for eight hours (overnight works well) and I found that they are not affected by water if you decide to leave them on longer. What I really like is that they do not contain any harsh ingredients, unlike the usual acne gels that dry up and irritate my skin.

I find these really useful for those summertime heat spots that don't seem to resolve. The Dream Dots keep the area clean and literally draw out the inflammation, and next morning my skin is well on its way to repair the problem. column6: Antifungal Soap with Tea Tree Oil, Helps Treat & Wash Away Athletes Foot, Ringworm, Nail Fungus, Jock Itch, Body Odor & Acne. Antibacterial Defense Against Bacteria Related Skin Irritations 9oz.
column13: This soap plus Aloe Vesta Antifungal Ointment cured my jock itch when other products didn't.
column14: i had recurring jock itch for the past two years.  never had jock itch or athletes foot before in my life, but I couldn't get rid of it.  I used all the over the counter chemical products such as Lamisil and they would help clear it up over a period of time but it kept coming back.  I decided to take a different course of action and got this Tea Tree soap and also  Aloe Vesta Antifungal Ointment.  I would wash my groin area twice a day with this product and then completely dry the are (I used a hair dryer much to the chagrin of my GF) and then apply the Aloe Vesta ointment.  Overall the products seemed much more natural than the brand name chemical creams but best of all IT WORKED. After about three weeks I was completely clear.  When its hot and muggy I just use the soap and I have not had another breakout since.

column6: Escali 100% Pure Badger Shaving Brush
column14: Essentially became only 50% useful after two to three weeks of use, at around 3 days between shaves. First lather on shave soap showed some brown oily residue, I figured since the brush was brand new I would have to break it in, but yet here I am months later and still brown residue coming off bristles. The bristles themselves are very coarse to the skin, especially for those who have sensitive skin and are likely to bleed during a shave. What did it in for me was that after about 6 uses, with typical lather technique, the middle part of the brush (essentially the core of the brush where most lather should be) became depressed into the brush, the bristles became tangled down there and that results in a garbage lather. Lastly, I feel the handle is too small as most of the lather created always drips down. Still using, but only until my Edwin Jagger Best badger brush arrives. You get what you pay for. Since badger brushes are graded by hair, it's like the three little pigs story. Don't start with the hay house (this brush) spend your 16$ and go to the next level.

column6: Garnier Intensive 7 Days SOS-Repair Hand Cream - Shea Butter (100ml)
column13: Soothes, protects and hydrates well whilst being quick absorbing too
column14:
'Intensive' skin care products are often thick, heavy creams that sit upon the skin, but this Garnier cream isn't like that at all. It's certainly quite thick, but it lives up to its 'fast absorbing' description.

It rubs in very quickly with absolutely no greasy feeling. It's virtually scent - free, so can be used by cooks in the kitchen without the worry of tainting food.

Although I don't have chapped hands, I had a couple of nicks to the skin when first testing this; it was soothing to apply with no stinging.
For those who like their products to have natural ingredients, this cream has three, namely shea butter, olive oil and apricot kernel oil.

The claim is that the skin hydrating properties remain even after hands are washed. I use moisturising handwash so this was a difficult claim to judge - it takes so little time to rub in that I found myself automatically applying an extra dab of cream anyway. Although it absorbs quickly, a little does go a long way with this cream.

The price of this cream compares very favourably with other high performance hand creams, the Garnier name being an established name of quality.
Summary: a pleasant, economical cream for dry skin that soothes, protects and hydrates well. I received this product to review without cost via the Amazon UK Vine Voices scheme but this is my honest and unbiased opinion.

column6: Venus Gillette Embrace Purple Razor, Womens Razors / Blades
column13: Makes my legs feel like dolphins
column14:
These are great. I continue to use the handle and buy refill cartridges, which are also available on Amazon (but you can use any Venus refills; they don't have to be Venus Embrace).

Once you start using 5 blades, it's so hard to go back. The moisture ribbon that surrounds the blades isn't a substitute for shaving cream, but it definitely helps give a closer shave. The handle has a comfortable no-slip grip and the head of the razor easily contours to your curves giving you a close shave even in tricky parts like knees and armpits.

With these, my legs feel like dolphins and my arm pits have no bumps or ingrown hairs. (bro tip: if you get bumps or ingrown hairs often, just quickly exfoliate your underarms with a face scrub or a loofa before you shave. It makes a HUGE difference, especially after doing it for a few weeks!)

Would definitely recommend these.

column6: TotLogic Leave In Conditioning & Detangling Spray - Naturally Scented - 8 fl oz
column13: Very light-weight conditioning spray with some detangling ability - has helped during pregnancy
column14: This leave in conditioner has been a life-saver during my pregnancy!  It's amazingly difficult to find a light, non-oily leave in conditioner that doesn't contain harmful chemicals, especially synthetic fragrance.  Since I've become pregnant, I've had to stop using ALL of my old haircare products, either because they contained phthalates or because they were too heavy for my now terribly oily scalp.  I have very long, thick hi-lighted hair that needs extra TLC a few inches from the scalp, but my oily scalp has been a MAJOR issue - it's like I'm a teenager again.  I started getting scalp acne, including painful cystic acne along the nape of my neck.  I had to stop using my extra-moisturizing conditioner, but that left me with knotted, dry ends.  This TotLogic leave in conditioner helped me find just the right balance and doesn't make my hair sticky or greasy, and it doesn't exacerbate my prenatal acne.  At first I wasn't sure about this product because it's almost like water, and I find it to be an okay but not great detangler; it does take a good bit of product to get the tangles out of thick adult hair, but while I'm dealing with this oily scalp problem and desire to keep all harmful stuff away while pregnant, I find it worth the extra time it takes to do the job.  I think this would be a perfect conditioning/detangling spray for a child, although I haven't used it for this purpose yet, and I plan on using this on my daughter when she needs it.  Unlike some reviewers, I don't find the smell off-putting at all - it's pleasant enough, very light and unnoticeable once hair is dry (and yes, my sense of smell is CRAZY right now).  I do still miss my Davines Nounou leave-in conditioner because it made my hair so silky and shiny, but if you need a very lightweight detangler without all the icky stuff found in typical products, whether it be for a child or because you're pregnant, you might give TotLogic a try.  I'm glad I did!

column6: LA Colors Jumbo Eye Shadow Eye Liner Pencil 24 Colors with Free 2 in 1 Pencil...
column14:
I used to use these. I got 7 pencils for $7.99 at Burke's. Some of them are not pigmented than others. I stopped using them because this are creamy eye-shadows and I prefer powder. Here is some info on some of the colors I had

Pink- not very pigmented but in the light shines and showed a pinkish tint..

Baby Blue- good pigmentation and would become even more pigmented the more I added..

Black- very dark gray looking but not at all like black shark skin shadow..

Grey- dark grey, very similar to the black, not good for blending with powders, especially white shadow..

Dark brown- this was a great shadow that brought out my blue eyes..

Lavender- also went well with my blue eyes and for some reason this color stayed on most of the day where as the other colors would come off in just a couple of hours..

Light green- smudged allot and wasn't as attractive in color as I thought it would be..

This is a pretty good deal but don't expect all day wear and keep in mind that you get what you pay for.

If you really want to try this product for yourself then I suggest you but it for this price because I stated above how much I paid for seven of them so this is a little bit better of a deal for 24 of them.

Recommendation: would recommend them for temporary use.

column13: Swept Away by my CitySwept by Bumble and Bumble
column14:
[[ASIN:B00ID0AZ2C Bumble and Bumble Bb City Swept Finish Hair Spray, 4 Ounce]] Aside from the fact that I was expecting a package at my door and not a padded envelope in my mailbox, and thought the shipping was taking a considerably long time,(don't check my mail daily) the envelope protected the B&B aerosol can adequately.

I had already used the spray at the salon where I get my hair cut and liked it because I don't have to put cream in my hands and mold and separate like a savant. I just lift my hair up from underneath and give it a light spray, the same on other side, and for bangs, after using a straight iron, I give them a slight messy look or "windblown" look and again a light spray, then quickly piece them apart how I like. The smell is kind of nice too.
My only complaint is that they are a bit outrageous with their pricing. $30 for a hairspray? I'd like to say I will be a loyal customer, but I'll have to start researching comparable products out there... like Redken which aren't cheap, but even they have promotions. I get 2 /33.8 fl.oz of shampoo and conditioner for for $35 and this spray is a measly 4 oz.
Bumble and Bumble...you need to reassess if you want to retain your customer base.

The moral of the story...track your shipping, so you can see how your item is being shipped.

From left to right:

The kind of dome brush I use for blush.

The flat brush I don't really use but can be used to apply concealer to small areas.
The thicker brush I use for highlighter, but can also be used for a more precise powder contour.
The flat top brushes I use to set foundation around my face. I have tried these for foundation but found that they are not dense enough.
The shorter dome brush I also use to apply blush or even bronzer.

column13: I loved that I could use Amazon prime along with fulfillment ...
column14:
I ordered this product though Beuty Superstore online. I loved that I could use Amazon prime along with fulfillment though Amazon, and Beauty Superstore's great price offer. Ok so now about the product:

Iâ€™m a 43-year-old woman. Due to allergies etc I stay away from food such as onions and other products that contain sulphur, which from what I read and hear is an integral element in hair growth. Because of that my hair generally is weak, thin, and falls out quite easily. Generally I use natural shampoo that contains something called â€œawlaâ€ which has generally strengthened my hair in comparison to what it is naturally. I wanted to order something different that would also give a little volume to my hair. My friend already uses this product and loves it. So after reading reviews I bought this product. This product has, over the last few days of use (approx. 5) at least, definitely improved the strength of my hair. I do realize its too early for a dramatic change, but I do feel that my hair is shedding a LOT less. When I comb it in the morning, I notice less hair coming out in the brush or even on the floor. Now I cannot say whether this product exclusively is the cause behind my hair not falling off or not because there are just too many factors involved in hair not shedding off. Also this product hasn't caused me itching or little blisters on my scalp which most other chemical products would typically cause. . However what I will definitely say is that this has to a large extent helped me. I will definitely update this review after around a month or two and hopefully the positive trend will continue.

column13: Great stuff, well worth the price.
column14:
I purchased this product for my 21 old daughter who has very light skin and burns easily; she has to wear sunscreen if she's out in the sun at all.

While the store shelves are full of sun-screen products that work well, I would never buy them. They are full of chemicals that have been directly linked to cancer.
Seems illogical to apply sunscreen to prevent skin cancer when the chemicals in the sunscreen have been directly linked to cancer! No thank you.

It took me a long time to find a product that is natural, free of harsh chemicals and most importantly - that works.
I've bought other "natural" sunscreen products but my daughter burned as much with them on as she did with no sunscreen at all.

This one made by Beauty by Earth is the best I've found. It is natural and it works well. After a full day on the beach with the outdoor temp being 95 and the sun index factor a 10 (on a scale of 0-10), including trips in and out of the salty ocean, my daughter had NO sunburn (except the base of her neck where she missed a spot and didn't apply it.......)

It's a bit pricy, but id much rather pay for this, than pay for junk that leads to cancer or to pay an oncologist to treat cancer....

Glad I found it; this will be our only sunscreen for as long as it is available.

column6: Arnica Oil Extract (Arnica Montana) - 2 oz/60 ml - Muscle & Joint Pain Treatment, Anti-inflammatory, Neck & Back Pain Relief, Sprains, Fractures, Sunburn Lotion, Bruise Treatment, Sore Muscles Remedy
column13: Wow, this actually WORKS!  Fast pain relief for muscle / tendon injury.
column14:
I have to say, I am frankly amazed at how well it works to relieve my muscle/tendon pain, and how quickly. I have been having pain in my forearm, and have started wearing a brace part time, which helps some, but not enough. I have been taking OTC pain relievers, but since the pain is continuing, I decided to look for other possible remedies besides numerous doses of pain pills every day. This arnica oil actually works, and reduces the pain in my forearm within minutes. The relief usually lasts for a couple hours. I am super impressed, even astounded, and wish I had tried an arnica product years ago.

I apply about 5-10 drops of the oil to my arm, and rub it in well. The relief is quick to follow. I am a first time arnica user, so I can't compare this particular product to any similar product. I chose this one because it seemed from reading descriptions and reviews that it was a stronger concentration.

The one thing I do NOT like about this product is the cap on the bottle. The press-flip cap sucks, if you plan to transport this anywhere or put it anywhere except sitting upright and untouched in your medicine cabinet. I want to carry it in my purse so I can use it whenever needed. Thankfully, I put it inside a plastic baggie and then into my purse, standing upright, but a little oil still leaked out into the baggie, despite the cap being tight and the flip top not being depressed. Also, the aperture (opening) on the cap is too big for something you are meant to dispense a few drops of at a time, as the product comes out far too fast, and invariably a few drops leak and run down the side of the bottle. Use care when dispensing. I think I will try and find a dropper top to replace the original cap. I would give the crummy cap 0 stars out of 5, however, I decided to review this product based on the medication quality only, and just mention the inadequate packaging in my review.

column14: I used to use Sen-Sen constantly, and I was really bummed when it was discontinued. I've since tried just about every similar product on the market, and for my purposes, KAOL is the closest match. It's certainly a very different flavor, but both have a similar pungent, herbal/earthy-toned licorice note. KAOL is also conveniently tiny like Sen-Sen, and it's similarly sugar/sweetener-free. I'll even go as far as to say I prefer KAOL, because it doesn't leave tiny dust crumbs like Sen-Sen did, and its packaging is far more durable while being similarly classy and timeless.

This is a very good blow dryer. It has three heat and two speed settings, and a cool shot button to help set your style. It's 1875 watts- so it's nice and strong though not as powerful my professional hair dryer that does dry my hair faster. But my hair has been getting split ends and damaged, so I love that this dryer is designed to protect against heat damage. Only time will tell if that feature works, but I sure need it. This also has the usual attachments that I never use but they look the same as what typically comes with a blow dryer. My biggest problem with blow dryers is the motor dies from not regularly cleaning the lint filter (which draws in dust and causes the motor to overheat). So one great feature is this Remington has a removable filter for easy cleaning, and that will definitely prolong the life of the hair dryer if the filter is cleaned out regularly.

My hair comes out smooth and nice with the Remington. My favorite part about the design is it's comfortable to hold, the controls are placed well for comfortable use and most of all it's super lightweight. Also, this dryer is not as loud as most others. It looks great in purple too. I do wish the cord was a little longer. It's long enough for plugging into a high outlet in a bathroom, but if I need to use a lower outlet in another room then the cord is too short for me to stand and dry my hair (though adequate if I sit down). I'm used to a longer cord, so others may not mind the cord length, but I'm taking one star off as I think the cord should be at least a foot longer. column6: Kids Tattoo Stencil Set: Best of GlitZGlam - HYPOALLERGENIC and DERMATOLOGIST TESTED! -Temporary Tattoos Stencils Set for children & teenagers
column14:
I received this in an order with a few other products, it was in a cellophane wrap with a resealable/easy access tab on the bottom. I will start this by saying when I purchased this stencil kit I was expecting a stencil like I used in school, similar to the picture on the package on one solid piece. So when the package was about the size of my hand I was surprised. These are individual stencils, one design per sheet and they are very nice sized, not too big, not too small. This particular pack of stencils had a lot of really cute designs that were both kid and adult friendly. The stencils themselves remind me of stickers, but they aren't paper. They're basically three pieces, a sticky clear sheet, a flexible, thin plastic piece that works as the actual stencil, and the white paper backing. You remove the white backing, apply the stencil to the skin (make sure it's clean and dry), get all of the bubbles out of the stencil itself and peel off the clear plastic covering. You have now applied your stencil. I found that it was very easy to apply and equally easy to remove, although you have to be careful when removing in order to maintain the beauty of the smaller details of the tattoo. I was disappointed to see that these are not reusable, they are one time use only. Of course being a frugal lady I did try to reuse one (on my daughter so it wasn't gross or anything haha) and I think it turned out okay. It didn't lay down well so there were definitely lumps and bumps but it was okay and would work in a pinch if you have two kids that want the same tattoo.

Pros: Sturdy, sticky, application and removal is simple. Fun variety of designs, something for everyone.
Cons: Nothing really, besides the fact that they are really one-time-use only

Overall this is a great product. I did receive this product for a discount in order to give my unbiased review. I'd recommend this product for all ages!

column14:
Like so many women, I'm always on the chase for the right concealer. For me, what it's come down to is providing soft coverage to take the "sting" out things I am not fond of, like dark circles, without becoming a facade of me.
I like to use this by dabbing in light feathery strokes under a BB cream or mineral powder. Depending on which BB cream, I might repeat layering on top lightly to try minimize anything "settling" in.
I also like to use this as a base for my lips, applying in a very sheer way it provides something to stick to, gives a fuller look and lets the color blossom.

Axe makes lots of good, dependable menâ€™s personal care products and Axe White Label 2 in 1 hair and body wash ranks among them. column6: Herbal Essences Ends on the Mend Keratin Serum, 4.2 FL OZ
column14:
i have long, thin hair. i struggle to find hair products that won't end up leaving my hair greasy. i saw this in the store and decided to try it. i already use herbal essences shampoo and conditioner so i knew this had to be a decent product. well, it exceeded my expectation! i have been using this for over a month and i can see the difference that it has made. since my hair is thin, i have a hard time brushing it because it gets tangled so easily. they way i use this product is after a shower, i wait until my hair is damp, pump some of the serum into my hand, rub my hands together and work this through my hair. i mainly focus on the ends, but do usually go halfway up my head. i probably use a total of 5-6 pumps. i wait a few more minutes and then brush my hair. before using this serum, brushing my hair would be such a hassle! i once timed myself and it took me 15 minutes to brush my hair while it was damp because of all the knots and tangles i had to get out. now it only takes 5-7 minutes to brush my hair. i am so happy i found this product and took a chance on it! the smell is amazing and long lasting, my hair is smoother and just looks healthier in general.

Edit: to upload pictures to show how shiny/sleek my hair is and that I no longer have split ends!

column6: Leomael naturals ivory shea butter
column14:
I've heard only good things about Shea Butter but only until now do I get to see for myself the effects personally. Taking out of the envelope it was delivered in, was the white zip lock type bag, and inside was another, sealed plastic one with the product. I was very happy that it was packaged this way, because when it arrived, it was squishy and watery! This is the way I've learned that for sure, that this product is truly organic and natural, because when in warm weather, the product will melt. It's quite fascinating! I know that coconut oil will do this as well.

I didn't want to be scooping the product out of the bag every single time I wanted to use it, so what I did was stick it in the freezer for two hours or so, found a container that would fit it, cut the plastic with a knife, and stuck it in the container! I left it in a warm spot, and the shea butter started melting again, fitting perfectly into the container. Now I can use it properly!

So far I have been using it as a body moisturizer, and it leaves my skin with a very pretty glow! I've never seen my skin below the neck look so dewy and fresh ... My face is already nice and dewy, but it always bothered me that my skin, no matter what I used on it, didn't have that same healthy shine! I'm also using it on my feet, as that is the place that needs the most hydration, and after just a few minutes of my skin soaking up the Shea Butter, I can definitely say that this is now one my miracle products. Shea butter literally IS skin food!!

As for any grittiness, it definitely is there... I initially thought it was because some parts might have been frozen, but when it melted completely, they were still there and I quickly realized I was mistaken. For that reason, I won't be using it on my face, as i'm very afraid of scarring. But to be honest, I expected the grittiness, as should have anyone who took away a star for it. It does say "unrefined" in the title for a reason. I will only be using this on my body, as that is more than good enough for me! I am truly very happy with this product.

This product was provided at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.ll only be using this on my body, as that is more than good enough for me! I am truly very happy with this product.

column14: [[VIDEOID:ba24b38831701b56ed947c8d17384ca4]]Honor Silicone Ring by HonorGear is a silicone wedding band made of medical grade silicone and perfect for those of us who want to show our committment to our marriage but have trouble wearing our normal wedding rings or wedding bands. It is great for those who work out and either don't want to lose their ring or damage it due to lifting weights. Honor's Eternity Ring is also perfect for people who work in a field where wearing your wedding ring endangers your life due to machinery, electricity, etc. Some companies forbid jewelry for this reason so this silicone ring would be perfect. I chose this ring in purple and love it because it has more of a girly feel (although it is geared towards men).    Personally, I can't wear my wedding ring due to painful/swollen joints so I love the fact that this ring gives me something to wear. For those of us with allergies, it's also hypoallergenic and should be safe to wear for most people. It can also be worn in water without any thought of damage and it will also dry so that you finger is not wet underneath. column13: Feels like a hard volcanic rock at first but turns into a super soft sponge after it's wet!
column14: I have never used this kind of sponge before and I was pretty excited when I received it. I came in a package in a clear package with directions and recommendations. I really like how I was able to tear the sealed package open to know that no one else had used this sponge (you never know!). When you first touch the sponge, it's hard as a rock and it definitely feels like a volcanic rock or something. I soaked this sponge for a few minutes in water to get it wet and its hard rock texture turned into a very soft texture. I use my Clarisonic on a daily basis but it's definitely a nice change to use a softer sponge instead to cleanse my face. This is perfect if you're breaking out and you don't want to irritate your acne and skin by rough cleansing. I squirted my cleansing directly onto my sponge and spread it evenly all over my face before working the product into my skin in circular motions. It's definitely very soft to the skin and feels very nice. column6: Garnier Hair Color Nutrisse Nourishing Color Creme
column14:
This product gets only 1 star from me.

The color was matched by my own perception in the store while comparing my color to the box, which was the closest match, and also by the color selector on Garnier's website matching tool before I even applied the color. I thought with the double assurance, what could go wrong? I was only wanting to color a few premature grey hairs!

I have long hair so I grabbed 2 boxes of the color 30, which is a dark brown.

My hair is virgin hair with no previous color added to it or modified in any way.

I followed all directions, which were simple. Apply it, wait, rinse, condition.

When I rinsed, it looked like my natural color, but I was horrified when my hair was completely dry the next morning. I wanted to cry. My hair looked brown but very lighter and with a major tint of orange.

How could a product that matched closely to my natural color make my hair LIGHTER? Well I don't have the answer, so I have no clue.

I will attach some photos which will show my natural roots against the boxed color. MAJOR difference.

Oh, and the greys were only covered for about a week. So all of this wrongdoing was done for absolutely nothing.

column6: Silver Tone Double Edge Blade Razor Shaver w Nonslip Metal Handle
column13: A good product from China? Definitely!
column14:
This razor is shipped from China so it took awhile to get, but still got it before promised date. I've been using this for about two weeks now.

First impression this razor feels heavy, surprisingly well made for what I paid. If bought in a store in the U.S. This feels like a 30 dollar razor. Nice ergonomics for my thick hands.

As for how it works? I let my beard grow for a few days, I looked like grizzly Adams by then. So I tried the razor hoping it wouldn't be too painful. Some cold water, thick beard Barbasol, and ten minutes later, my chubby face is as smooth as a baby's bottom. No nicks, very little deep pulling.

Couple of days later my five o clock shadow is back, I'm quite hairy, but not much so the double edge went pretty deep. Replacement blades is the only draw back, about 16 bucks a pack. Tip of the day. Keep the blade dry after use by removing it after use and dry them thoroughly each time and each blade should last more than a few months.

column6: 3D Fiber Lash Mascara, 300X Fiber Mascara by Lash Factory - Our Best 3D Fiber Lashes - Waterproof, Smudge-Proof, No Clump, Long Lasting, 3D Mascara
column13: Works well for lighter colored eye lashes
column14:
I have been told by so many people that I need to try 3D fiber mascara. My friends are always looking to find a local sales person to buy it from and act like they just can't live without it. So I decided to give it a go. I was a bit surprised to find out that you use it along with regular mascara. The product is easy enough to apply. You put on regular mascara, then a coat of the gel (black like mascara) then a coating of the fibers. The fibers look like tiny chopped off pieces of lint (but not in a ball) Then another coat of the gel. It says apply as many coats as needed. I gave it a shot and I think it did well for some extra volume, but I don't see a huge difference. I put regular mascara on one eye and used the 3D on the other. I guess if you have thin eye lashes it will help out a lot, but I didn't see a huge length difference. The little pieces fell off a couple times before I got the gel on and fell in my eye, which didn't hurt too bad, so try and move quickly and not blink. I see why my friends like it as a few of them have very sparse lashes, so it helps them, but I don't see a huge difference for myself. My husband couldn't guess which eye had my regular cover girl and which eye had the 3D.

Update: My sister in law loves it. She says she can see a big difference in her eyelashes. She has light colored lashes and says this helps her out. The product works well for her, so I am updating this review.

*I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE TO TRY OUT IN EXCHANGE FOR AN HONEST AND UNBIASED REVIEW. EVERYTHING IN THIS REVIEW IS MY OWN AND IN NO WAY INFLUENCED.

column6: Mascara - Best 3D Fiber Lash Mascara Set For Thickening & Lengthening Eyelashes By Up To 300%-Safe For Sensitive Eyes- Non Toxic All Natural Ingredients- Herbal -No Clumps -Get Your Dream Lashes Now!
column13: Best fiber lashes i ever used
column14: To give you a little background on myself, I'm a freelance makeup artist who worked for sephora for 5 years, and on my own for an additional 5. I've tried pretty much all the mascaras sephora carries, and then also shop at department stores, ulta, and occasionally a drugstore I even included a pic of the current mascaras I'm using, I normally switch back and forth, or use a combo of two or three, this is my current batch. This mascara is the s***. Excuse my language, but before this one, one of my favorite mascaras was a line that rhythms with "Too Maced" and it was their two part mascara, with the first one being a normal mascara, and the second being a bottle of white fibers you stacked on top. Now I loved this mascara, it gives the biggest longest lashes I had ever gotten, not wearing fake lashes, but my issue was it was a huge pain in butt to take off So I used it for special occasions, when I wanted to look good, but I was gonna have to spend an hour taking off my make up anyway. This mascara is WAY easier to take off, and they made the fibers black, which was a "duh" moment for me, like of course make it black, you're gonna paint over it anyway! So this 3d fiber mascara is a little tricky to put on at first (unless you've used the other brands, then it's the same thing) you first put on a layer of the regular black mascara (transplanting gel I think they call it) and IMMEDIATELY take the fibers and brush it on, over and under You'll see the fibers stick and your lashes will look twice as big soon as you do it Then I move to the next eye, repeat the process, this gives the gel and fibers a second to dry and stick together.. Then you can't repeat the process as many times as you want, you can get them really quite big, but make sure you seal the fibers in with a final coat of the gel mascara If you don't you'll have little black fibers all over your face and they aren't cute, or easy to get off, without getting rid of the rest of your makeup. column6: Remington D3190A Damage Control Ceramic Hair Dryer, Ionic Dryer, Hair Dryer, Purple
column13: Love the \cool shot\" feature and that the filter is cleanable!"
column14:
Let me start with the removable filter which allows you to clean the dust out, my previous dryers did not have this option and the filter would clog diminishing the airflow and the drying ability. That is why this is such an important feature to me,you would think all hair dryers would have it!
Now to its features: it has 3 heat settings and 2 power settings (*wish there were 3!)
annnd a "cool shot" which Iove, Love, LOVE! I have very thin, fine hair and when I set my hair with heat rollers I use the "cool shot" feature to speed up the "set" and my curls stay in longer as the hair is more cooled down before I take the rollers out so the curls don't fall out as quickly as they used to, my set lasts longer.
I use the concentrator but have no need for the diffuser but if you are naturally curly it is a nice attachment to have.
It has the heat protection "ionic technology" that helps keep your hair frizz and fly away free, dries hair fast (I have long hair) and doesn't tangle it up when just doing a blow dry and not setting my curls.
It has a 2 year warranty and is at a GREAT price for what you get. I would recommend this dryer.

column6: Royie Temporary Hair Chalk Set Non-toxic Rainbow Colored Dye Pastel 24 | 32 Piece Kit
column14:
Alright. So I think I have learned a lot from my experience with this hair chalk.

The main lesson learned is that, depending on your hair type, you WILL get different results: If you have darker hair, you should wet your hair and the chalk and it should show up, but blonde hair is different. Ideally, you shouldn't use water because you run the risk of staining our hair (but some blonde hair doesn't absorb color well, so it does really depend on knowing your hair). My hair always absorbs color, so I tried to do it dry and it didn't work super well, and it still ended up staining my hair the lavender color of the chalk (but it came out in two washes, so it wasn't a big deal).

Also, I used half a stick of lavender on just one streak of hair by my face because I have so much hair, so this product is ideal for shorter hair and thin streaks.

Finally, I would recommend wearing gloves because it gets all over your hands (especially if you are wetting your hair or chalk). Plus, I would do this over a sink because the chalk will fall around you.

I think this would be fun for kids who want funky streaks in their hair :)! I think I'll use this when I babysit, just probably not for myself due to my hair not being super compatible with their temporary coloring product.

Hope this was helpful!

column6: Remington PF7200 F2 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Black
column14:
This Remington F2 foil shaver is a good lightweight portable shaver which can easily be carried on business trips. For short business trips, my husband can pack the F2 with him and, fully charged, he can easily travel multiple days without worrying about needing to recharge it. This shaver has a 30 minute runtime, and for him as he has a beard, that is easily a week's worth of shaving.

The pop-up trimmer works well to trim tray hairs on his beard and sideburns, while the foil shaver does an good job on his neck and cheek areas that he shaves regularly. The result on his neck is remarkably smooth for an inexpensive shaver.

Overall, this is a good value for a lightweight and inexpensive shaver. It works well on my husband's face and he assures me that it would work well for most men looking for a nice basic shaver or for someone looking to give an inexpensive gift.
