column6: By Terry Touche Veloutee Highlighting Concealer Brush, No. 01 Porcelain, 0.22 Ounce
column14: I have had very dark (quoting medical professional) under eye circles since my early teens.  I have used every imagineable concealer, corrector + concealer, powder 'concealer', under eye brightener, etc.  For literally decades I accepted the caking and more than gradual aging not to mention the magnified look of crepiness once I started using readers.  Initially received this product as a 2 for 1 through a shopping network.  Zero issues with the case or delivery system.  My two tubes lasted almost a year.  I apply to the back of my hand then use a concealer brush or fingertip to apply under eyes, around the nose, and very lightly on broken capillaries or spots.  The texture of my under eye skin has greatly improved even though I have always used high end eye serum/cream.  This concealer is more of a natural looking camouflage.  On my face I apply a similar type of serum foundation then the Touche Veloutee where needed.  Under eyes I apply directly to the dark areas, no foundation or powder.  On eyelids less is best to neutralize tea stains and redness.  Wish the 2 for 1 offer was still available.  Paying the full price now because it is that great.  To the person who complained about too many clicks to get the product out, send back for an exchange.  Normally one pump lasts thru multiple applications.  One of my tubes dried out after spending the summer in a cottage without AC.  The other one stayed perfect until it was completely empty.

column6: Probelle All Natural Fungal Nail Treatment, Clear, .5 Fluid Ounce
column14:
I've had nail fungus for years and have battled it half-heartedly every so often. This time I decided that I will make more of an effort and really get rid of it by ensuring that I was faithful and aggressive using the products every day. I purchased several nail fungus treatments including a foot soak. I'd often see reviews how the toenails take six to eight months to grow out and never agreed with it. My toenails always grew quickly even when removing the brown hardened and brittle nails from the nail bed. It wasn't unusual for it to grow back within a couple of weeks. I guess it grew quickly because of the fungus.

It's been a month between this product and another product that smells like oregano along with the foot soak. My nails have not grown back yet. My big toe bed on my right foot was always the worst and when clipping the brown nails, you could see that the toe bed was brown/black and the fungus was part of the skin. I was able to do this because most of the nail separated from the toe bed. Since most of my toenail on my right foot is gone I can see the results more quickly than the other toes. The brown/black used to run from the bottom to the top, but now it's only at the bottom and I can see that the fungus goes really deep. I put a Band-Aid on to protect my exposed toe bed during the day after I allow the product to dry.

I can't believe my nails haven't grown back yet.I guess the fungus is being killed off and once that happens my nails will start to grow back. I'll update again in six months.

column6: DermOrganic Firm Hold Volume Foam 5oz
column14:
This product works nicely for thin hair and kudos to brands, like this one, for limiting the chemicals... But the Ingredients List should be listed for consumers. It's not 100% organic obviously so consumers should naturally expect some chemical derivatives. For those who care for more info or who assume it's free of harsh chemicals, here's the list with a breakdown of the mysterious items:

Aqua/Eau/Water,

PVP Copolymer: A petrolium derived chemical.

Alkylpolyglucosides: Surfactant derived from sugar and fats.

Disodium Cocoyl Glutamate: Extraction process where the oil is separated out for use with petrochemicals and other chemical solvents. The extraction is followed by extensive processing and forced reactions with synthetic chemicals (usually several reactions with several chemicals), which transforms the ingredient until a foam boosting chemical surfactant is produced.

Polysorbate-20: A chemical emulsifier regarded as safe.

Methyl Gluceth-20 (derived from corn starch/corn sugars),

Ethylhexyl Methoxycinnamate: A chemical UV Filter

Organic Argania Spinosa (Argan) Kernel Oil,
Organic Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Extract,
Organic Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Extract (UV Inhibitors),
Rice Amino Acids,

PCA: Sodium

Panthenol B5,
Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E),
Glycereth-2 Cocoate & Benzoic Acid,

Parfum/Fragrance: Not specified so most likely chemical based.

column6: Philips Norelco BeardTrimmer 5100, for beard stubble and mustache
column13: the head for the detail edge
column14:
I have only owned one other beard trimmer...a Remington from Costco. I had nothing to compare to, and thought that making multiple passes through my moderately thick beard and mustache were normal, and that pulling hair, particularly on the mustache was normal. When the Remington gave up I had no idea the number of choices out there!.....and multiple ones from the same brand. There are so many reviews where people say they would never own a Norelco, Panasonic, Wahl etc again, and many more who said it was the best trimmer they ever owned. Reviews from Men's Health and other sites were also all over the map. So here is a review to help you decide.
I finally decided on this trimmer based on moderate price, well over 55% 5 star reviews and not too many 1 star reviews.
I'M GLAD I took the chance! This little beauty is great!

PROS
1. The obvious..a great one pass (maybe two in a couple places), very even, non pulling shave. (I mean, isn't that the real test?)
2. Simple simple simple! I really like a narrow detail side for above my lip, over my ears (no I don't use it for haircut, just a little touch up before the regular haircut) so having the head rotate into position smoothly and securely, without having to CHANGE heads is great! (The two heads are on the same non-removable end--very secure)
3. Also on the simple side---ONE comb! I was forever trying to read the small length markings on the TWO double sided combs on the old one, and they didn't snap on and off easily. You just put the one ONE comb on and adjust from a half inch or so beard, all the way down to a 1 or 2 day stubble look depending on how fast your beard grows. There are 17 selections, with many short selections.The rotating dial is smooth to operate, with detentes that let you know that you are "on" the setting. Once there it stays put.
4. The comb only has to be removed when you rotate the head....not to change lengths. It looked too rounded at first, and the combs too thick. Not so. because of the design it doesn't poke, and separates the hairs nicely. The comb attaches firmly into the trimmer, and comes on and off in such a way as to not stress the plastic.
5. There is a charge indicator, and the charger charges fast. The razor CAN be used while it is charging.
6. Slender, ergonomic design, but not lightweight- just the right weight in the hand---really well made.
7. It's washable--not important for me, but might be for some.
8. Blades don't need oil
9. It's AMAZON...no my name is not Jeff Bezos, and I own no stock. I had finally decided to return to Costco and buy whatever they had...It was a Norelco 7500 which they had at least 10 of the day before. In it's place were TWO Norelco electric razors (not capable of beard trimming) and a Wahl multipiece, in case you want to go to work for Supercuts. Ah, the old Costco curse--buy it when you see it--it may not be there by the time you circle the warehouse! BUT, I went home, ordered from AMAZON about 8PM and it was (no joke!) on my doorstep at 10AM the next morning with free shipping.
CONS
1. No stand---not a con for me---I like an uncluttered counter. My old one HAD to charge in the stand, so I left it out sitting. This one I just put in the drawer.
2. No multiple attachments--again, not a con for me. I didn't want a combination can opener- beard trimmer, or a bag of attachments, or a stand where they always fall off. I suppose a nose hair trimmer would be nice, but I don't need one. And then, you would lose the simplicity of the rotating permanently attached head. Just pick up a nose hair trimmer guys. Amazon has them for as low as $7.75 (Wahl) and Hammacher Schlemmer has what looks like an amazing one for $20 if you have barbed wire growing out of your nose. I was just genetically blessed with no back hair or nose hair--but I can empathize!
3. No laser. Really guys, a laser!I'm a gadget guy, but even I couldn't see the use of that! Well maybe if I had multiple weird beard/goatee angles. But then I'd feel like keeping it in my tool box, and who wants to run to the garage every time you need a shave?

In conclusion---are there better trimmers out there? I don't know, maybe, but I can't imagine a simpler one that does such a great job---oh did I say it was powerful too? I do have to say I was a little curious to see what Norelco's $200 beard trimmer must be like, but not curious enough to lay out that kind of money. this one is just perfect.

column6: Kyoku Water Body Lotion for Men, 8.45 Fluid Ounce
column13: Softening, but a tad greasy and lacks any cooling sensation.
column14:
The lotion comes with both the standard cap shown and a pump -- which I prefer to use. The standard cap isn't terribly hard to use, but due to the shape of the durable, firm bottle of the lotion, it is a bit inconvenient and awkward to squeeze the lotion out. Replacing it with the pump made the lotion come out effortlessly and much easier. The lotion itself smells pleasant -- light, clean, and not overwhelmingly strong. I was actually expecting a bit more of a masculine touch to it, but it's not feminine either so I'm okay with the smell. It's also described with a light citrus smell, but I can't really tell if it's even there; the cooling sensation also isn't there, which is a bit disappointing considering that's how the Water is advertised. Applying the lotion definitely leaves skin smooth and soft but there is also a bit of greasiness -- not much, but still noticeable.

I received this lotion at a discounted price in exchange for a fair and honest review.

column13: I am hardly a wimp but this was so painful when removing it that my eye's watered something fierce ...
column14: OK, this was a difficult one to rate.  This was my first experience with waxing and I expected that there might be some discomfort and/or pain.  I also noted other users saying how messy it was to use, yep that it was however, it did indeed remove the unwanted hairs (above lip).  On the other hand the pain was excruciating!  I am hardly a wimp but this was so painful when removing it that my eye's watered something fierce from the pain.  It looked like I was crying.  It didn't leave any red marks and it removed 99% of all unwanted hairs.  Only a few remained to be plucked.  I would use this again if it wasn't for the pain.  It does say to press on the skin afterwards to lessen the pain but that is only temporary relief.  Four hours later, it was still painful but to the point I could ignore it easily.  Too bad, I really like how well it works but don't know if I'll use it again due to the pain.  Plucking is far less painful for me.

column6: Philips Norelco BeardTrimmer 7300, vacuum trimmer with adjustable length settings (Model # QT4070/41)
column13: The battery life is good - I only have to charge this every couple ...
column14:
Pros: The battery life is good - I only have to charge this every couple of weeks using it every other day. The adjustable length is quite nice as well, especially with the digital display. The trimmer is also quite comfortable to use. This trimmer does the job decently well, but several gripes lower the rating.

Cons: The vacuum collects some hair, but leaves a lot in the sink (even if you clean out the chamber between trimmings). It's better than a regular trimmer in this regard, but not quite as good as I'd hoped. The closure for the hair collection chamber is poorly designed - a small plastic tab holds it closed and mine broke off after about a month of gentle use. I now hold the door closed with a hair elastic which works okay, but not great. As for cutting quality, I find that I need to go over the same area several times to avoid leaving stray long hairs and the cut is not the cleanest. I suspect sharper blades would help here.

Overall: This trimmer does a fine job for the price, but when it fully breaks I'll be looking for other options.

This 6 piece brush set feels like the high end brushes without the high end price.

For my mineral powder foundation I used the bigger fluffy face brush.
For my cheeks I used the blush face brush and then used the same brush for my highlighter.
Now when I used the shadow brush included, I noticed it was not a big brush but a small one that can also be used for detailing but it worked well packing applying the color on my lids.
The fluffy blending brush was soft and it did a nice job of blending and for adding my browbone color.
The liner brush in this set can also be used for the brows but I chose to use it for my purple liner and the results were great.

column13: Great colour, but average in comparison
column14: I had received this product from BzzAgent as part of a promotion from the brand. I had heard of the Vidal Sassoon London Luxe dye before entering the campaign. Specifically, I've heard great reviews of the shade London Lilac and had even considered choosing the shade myself to try. However, since I'm currently in a nursing program, the shade seemed too bold, so I had chose Dark Royal Chestnut instead. I had tried several brands of at home hair kits before. In comparison I found Vidal Sassoon London Luxe to be average. The method of application was like most brands, but I personally prefer a mousse or foam application instead of the cream consistency, since it's easier and quicker to apply. The colour pay off is great and it gave me a vibrant brown shade. There were no streaks or patches and the colour applied evenly. There's nothing bad to say about this product. It delivered as I expected and nothing bad or good stood out. I did notice however the retain price of this product, which is around $12, even though most drug store dye kits are often on sale to around $6. Honestly, I don't think I'll find myself purchasing this in the future, although I am REALLY tempted to the London Lilac, so that will be the only reason if I ever purchase this.

column6: Got2b Powder'ful Volumizing Styling Powder
column14:
If you're skeptical about this product, don't be. It absolutely works as advertised. I have noticed some reviewers seem to be confused by the fact that this is a powder, and they assume it is a dry shampoo. It is NOT a dry shampoo. The product will probably allow you to keep a style overnight, but it is definitely a volumizer that should be applied either directly to your ROOTS not the entire hair shaft or to your fingers, which you then distribute where you want it on your roots. If you just shake it all over and expect it to work, it won't. It will make your hair coarse and slightly sticky.

How I use it on short, fine hair: I apply gel or spraygel to damp hair, then blowdry as usual. Then I apply this powder to my crown and the back/top of my head to create some lift. I sometimes even do spot applications if my hair is flatter in one spot than the other. Then spray, and I'm done! That's it. No need to blow this dry like a spray-in root lifter.

Do yourself a favor and give this a shot. I would suggest shopping around to major drugstores and local retailers to get the best price, but this product goes a long way with a little applied, so it should last awhile. Also, it is a smallish can, perfect for traveling or carrying in a purse for quick touchups (although it works all day--I've never had to use it for a touchup).

column6: Hylands Hylands Calms Forte Sleep Aid
column13: They're great before again before an audition or work presentation
column14:
I use these for anxiety and stress management. I suffer from mild generalized and social anxiety, so I pop one in every morning and can really tell the difference on the days when I forget to take one. They're great before again before an audition or work presentation, and help with flying and road trips since I tend to get motion sick. I also take three before bed to help my mind calm down a bit and have found that they do help me fall and stay asleep. Its great because they are non-habit forming, and I haven't experienced any negative side effects (knock on wood). Its also great because i can take as many as I need through out the day and not have to worry about overdosing ect, however I have found that taking more than three at a time isn't really more effective.

Calms Forte is not a sedative and is not meant to work like ambien or another sleeping pill of that variety. Its possible that people are confused over how they are marketed as a sleep aid, when the effects they provide (for me at least) are the relief of tension and anxiety, which then help me sleep better. Its not going to knock you out though, if thats what your looking for.

column13: I use this with other products..
column14:
After having several gel manicures that lifted in a week, I picked at, my nails were paper thin... I tried this because a friend had it. I didn't love the color she had, but my nails were strong. I went to Amazon, read the reviews and got the idea to just use the top coat (step 3-glaze). I read reviews for other products too and came up with this routine that has made nails stronger than ever before, even when I had a new gel manicure.
2 coats of OPI Nail Envy... then 1 or 2 coats of my color (not L'Oreal's gel), then a coat of L'Oreal Step3 glaze. A day or 2 later I add another coat of OPI Nail Envy or the Step 3. My nails are healthier than they've ever been.

column13: My skin looks great, feels hydrated and some of those very fine ...
column14: Ladies should not neglect the delicate skin on their necks and décolletage, but applying really expensive face creams there feels extravagent. Based on the reviews and ingredients I decided to try this cream. I recognize the ingredients, and the smell, which is not unpleasant. It has not irritated my sensitive skin, and keeps the moisture level high. I apply this to my neck, décolletage and the backs of my hands, then usually put another cream over it, especially in winter, to lock in the moisture. My skin looks great, feels hydrated and some of those very fine lines that middle aged ladies start finding on their décolletage have been reduced. It is not a miracle cream, but I try many creams in my quest to defy the appearance of age, and this is my second bottle, which means that I'm happy with the performance, and after running out of the original bottle, I noticed its absence. I do recommend this product for its natural ingredients, no nonsense packaging and a great price! I have not used it on my face, so I cannot attest to its performance in that area.

column6: All Natural SPF 30 Water Resistant Sunscreen by Tropical Sands, Reef Safe Zinc Oxide Sunscreen
column13: I only use this in natural bodies of water...
column14:
On one hand, I like the lack of hazardous chemicals. This sunblock is deemed acceptable for use at many parks and resorts where they care about reef protection, so I like that about it. However, that's basically the only thing I like about it.

The scent is very similar to Juicy Fruit gum, and it got annoying pretty fast. The texture is very greasy and pasty, and it did't really rub in the way normal sunblock does. You'd have to wash your hands after applying it, because it feels pretty gross until you do. It's very thick and white, and we had a hard time keeping it from getting all over our swimsuits.

I also didn't like the packaging, as the sunblock is quite thick, and once the bottle is around half full, it gets hard to get it out. A tube that can be flattened would be much easier. Still, the drawbacks are worth it if you're going to be swimming in a body of water where other creatures are affected by your choice of sunscreen. I definitely won't use it in pools, though.

column14:
I have ordered several products from FOXBRIM. I have found all of them to be high quality and effective. As for this Lavender I found it to be refreshing and the fact its natural makes it even better. I have bought the products I have from them because of what's listed on the front label. However, the back of the label is where I find most of the products I get even excited over. Ingredients like Witch Hazel, Vitamin C, Organic Aloe Vera, Yucca, Sage, Pomegranate, and other all natural healthy for the skin and body ingredients.
I keep mine in my crochet bag. I crochet all day, because I have an Etsy shop I have to keep stocked, so I often crochet all night. Making me feel and look run down. He lavender refreshes my skin and it also helps me stay calm, so I ca go to sleep when I'm done, instead of having to wind down.
Keep this in your bag to use throughout the day. Shake well to mix the ingredients. They separate a bit when sitting for a while.. Shaking insures you get the right combination of all of them.. I donâ€™t like saying I LOVE THIS!, because everyone seems to say the same thing. But I can say I LOVE LAVENDER!! And this smells like real fresh lavender when shaken and sprayed.
I love the items this company put out so far. I am looking forward to trying more of them.

column13: it seems fine. As others have mentioned I too have noticed ...
column14:
I know a lot of people have had issues with this new replacement blade... but for me, it seems fine. As others have mentioned I too have noticed that it does seem to pull SLIGHTLY more then my old blades... I usually shave every day and don't notice it. It's fine. However if I skip a day, I notice it. If I skip 2 or more days (which I have not yet) I'm sure I'll really notice it.

For those of us who shave every day and don't have THICK hair, this blade works fine. I can see how others with thicker hair have had issues. And as others mentioned they did change the way it works. They do give you the orange blade remover in here, but I don't have a reason to ever remove the blades (and you honestly don't need the tool).

People say it's easier to remove the cover now to get to the blades... okay. I find it no different then the old design. Maybe quicker, easier to remove everything since theres no hinge, who knows...

Anyway, I gave it 3/5 because it does work fine, however there is a different in blade quality over the other blades. But it's still a fine value.

column6: Super 6 Serum- w Vitamin C 22% + Hyaluronic Acid + 2.5% Retinol + CoQ10 for 6X Anti-Aging Benefits w Best Natural Astaxanthin & Niacinamide to Fight Wrinkles, Fine Lines, Acne & Spotsâ€¦
column14:
I ordered this product in early June and have used it every night since it came in. I feel that two months is plenty of time to figure out whether a product is working for you. For me, this one did not.

Before giving this a try I was using a popular Korean vitamin C serum that was very effective at brightening my skin and fading out dark spots. It did sting a bit upon application and the delivery time from overseas was long, so I wanted to try something different. I settled on the Super 6 Serum because not only did it contain the vitamin C I was after, it also contained other beneficial ingredients that I hoped would address other skin care concerns I have.

I liked that it didn't sting when I applied it. I liked that even though it is a bright orange color, it didn't stain or color my skin. I liked that it didn't break me out. I liked that it absorbed quickly and didn't leave my skin feeling sticky. What I didn't like was that it didn't seem to do much. I wasn't expecting a miracle: a little skin brightening, some help fading dark spots, maybe a bit of softening for the fine lines I'm starting to get around my eyes or at least some help preventing new ones. This product didn't seem to work very well for me in any of those areas.

column6: Panasonic ES-RT51-S Arc3 Wet/Dry 3-Blade Cordless Electric Razor
column13: Works reliably, but not the best cut.
column14:
I love Panasonic stuff normally, but this isn't about what I love. It's about what you, the informed consumer, should buy. So, if I had it to do over again, I'd do more research and get a better model. It's decent, but just that. My old rotary Norelcos cut better and shave smoother, and one of those sounds like it's ready to explode.

I think this shaver is built well. Feels solid. This is something I've noticed from Panasonic for many years and one of the reasons I bought it, as they rarely make anything that isn't good. But when you switch it on, especially after a full charge, it basically sounds like it's running at about a hundred thousand RPM, and gives you sort of a lackluster cut. Multiple passes over the same area. Really hard to get a decent shave on the neck. The flip-out trimmer is also not a very aggressive cutter, but it's fine inasmuch as it won't let you get too out-of-control on your moustache. Other reviewers have mentioned a "linear motor" available on higher-end models, so they may do a better job. My experience so far leads me to believe rotaries cut better, or at least faster.

column13: Great alternative to a typical circlating brush
column14:
[[VIDEOID:ddefbba64eefa19a2ff0ea8af60539bd]] I was very excited to try this Sonic Face Cleaning Brush. It was packaged nicely and tightly in a good box (great for gift giving I think) It came with a small instruction 'book', headband, charger, and the cleaning brush itself.

A big point in this for me was- Most cleaning brushes that rotate or have that mechanism can not be used with cleansers that have exfoliating beads due to the right of those beads getting into the motor, I don't have to worry about that with this. I think it's also a good option for someone with sensitive skin who may not do well with the regular fiber bristles.

I tried it out right away this is what I noticed-
The silicone actually gives a great grip even when wet.
The \\\bristles\\\\\" are nice and firm but still flexible to get a nice lather going.
The on button is centered and easy to find and push.
The adjustable vibration levels are a really great feature for me!
The tapered top is great for getting right up on my hairline where I seem to sweat a lot and need that cleaning power.

So far it has held a nice charge for me. The fact that it is rechargeable is a huge bonus in my book- not having to deal with it dying and not having spare batteries.
It is super easy to clean, super easy to charge.

I received this product discounted in exchange for an honest and unbiased review."

column6: Maybelline New York Lash Sensational Mascara
column14: This mascara doesn't hold the curl in my lashes at all.  And it doesn't give me much volume either.  Like almost all waterproof formulas, you can't apply more than one thick coat otherwise your lashes will get really clumpy.  But my other waterproof mascara does hold the curl all day so this one was a true disappointment.  The brush doesn't reach every lash and I found myself really struggling to get good coverage.  The color is nice and dark which is the only good thing I can say for it.  Even with a thin coat, there were some clumps and too much mascara builds up on the tip of the wand.  My regular waterproof mascara is The Rocket and although I'm not a fan of the brush, it does build considerable volume without clumps.  It also holds the curl.  This may be a result of the shape of the brush or because it's a totally different formula, I'm not sure which.  I think it's unlikely that Maybelline has numerous waterproof formulas.  It's more like they only have one and simply offer different brush styles.  Whatever the case may be, I get more volume and length with Rocket than with Lash Sensational.  If I can only apply one coat, I want to make sure each and every lash is coated and has maximum volume and length.  I can actually apply two thin coats of Rocket because it seems to take a little longer to dry (which is a good thing).  I use the Diorshow lash primer and then Rocket (Diorshow mascara sucks, btw) and I get full, dark lashes that look like falsies.  My lashes may have thinned with age, but they're still very long so I need volume the most.  Rocket is my go-to product and I'm sorry I wasted my money on Lash Sensational.  I may be looking for a mascara unicorn but there's bound to be a waterproof formula that permits several coats and still holds a curl.  So I'm still searching.  In the meantime, I'm sticking with Rocket because I refuse to spend big money on a product that only lasts three months.  For now, Rocket is the winner.

column13: Fantastic product value in a class of superior designed razors
column14:
First of all, this style of razor is superior and highly cost effective. To achieve a great shave, you need a sharp blade. All 5 blades does is spread out the contract area, it does not increase shave quality. One blade that is angled properly, easy to keep dry and replace, and infinitely cheaper will serve you just as well.

When you buy those fancy multi blade razors, ask you really get for your money is that fancy snap on ability.

As far as two sided, single blade safety razors go, this one is of particularly high value for the money. To a certain extent, any razor of this design with the right angles and ease of use will fit the bill, but shaveology has really stepped it up with extra quality blades, a drying cloth and simple, high quality, travel sheath.

At the price I payed, I can't imagine higher value.

column13: I can see the results already...
column14: I used to get some freckles every summer, mostly noticeable on my hands, but as I got older they stayed around longer, were bigger, and I think some people call them age spots instead of freckles now (although I don't like to call them that). I bought this anti aging serum hoping to lighten those spots. I took a photo of my hand after applying the serum a couple of times and then again a few days later. The spots are definitely lighter than before I started applying the serum but in the photos I cannot see a lot of difference.  There were no instructions included in the packaging or on the bottle about applying the serum but I remembered that on the listing it was called facial serum and that it was supposed to reduce fine lines and wrinkles.  I decided to see how the serum worked on the lines around my mouth. So this morning after washing my face I took a photo and then after applying the serum I took another photo a few minutes later. This time I not only saw my lines and wrinkles smoothing out, it shows in the photos.  I don't know if this is just a temporary reduction in the appearance of the lines and wrinkles or if I continue to use the serum it will make my skin look younger but I really like what it's doing so far.  I received this product at a discount in exchange for an honest and unbiased review but I like the results I'm getting and will continue to use the product.

column6: Be Natural Organics HaloSpa Advanced Cleansing Facial Brush and Micro-Exfoliating System
column13: 4-in-1 Cleansing Brush for 1/4 the price of Clairsonic brush! Great Deal!
column14:
I am a huge fan of cleansing facial brushes. Washing with your hands or a washcloth just cannot compete with the cleansing and exfoliating ability of a facial brush. The gentle bristles exfoliate dead skin and reduces blackheads, deep cleanse pores, and remove makeup, sweat, oil, and dirt. If you haven't used a facial cleansing brush before, trust me when I say that once you cleanse with a brush, you will never want to go back to washing with your hands or with a wash cloth.

A Clairsonic facial brush will run you around $100, and a Clinque facial brush around $90. Luckily, HaloSpa offers this awesome 4-in-1 cleaning brush for a fraction of the cost of one of those name brand brushes.

The HaloSpa cleansing brush is cordless and runs on 4 AA batteries. It is water-resistant and safe to use in the shower - just don't submerge it in water.

HaloSpa's cleansing brush comes with 4 attachments:
an exfoliating facial cleansing brush for deep cleansing and exfoliating your face
a large body brush for exfoliating dead skin and deep cleansing your body
a facial sponge for cleansing sensitive skin or for applying serum or moisturizer
and a pumice stone for buffing away calluses and dead skin

I use the facial cleansing brush for washing my face in the am and pm daily. My skin feels so fresh and clean after cleansing - I love it. I use the body brush bi-weekly to exfoliate my entire body in the shower. After the shower I drench my body in lotion and my skin is oh-so-soft. Love it. I have also found that the body brush is great for exfoliating my legs and underarms before I shave. It helps me get a nice, close shave and leaves my skin feeling extra smooth. Also, I tend to get ingrown hairs and exfoliating with the brush prior to shaving helps to keep them astray.

So, for about a quarter of the price of one of the name brand facial brushes you can purchase a cleansing brush that serves 4 purposes. The HaloSpa Advanced Cleansing Facial Brush and Micro-Exfoliating System is truly a great deal and I would absolutely recommend it.

column6: Nixoderm For Skin Problems Cream (Pack-3) 17.7 Grams
column14: This stuff is really amazing. I have had adult acne for about 15+ years now that had only improved slightly based on various products I have tried. I have spent so much money on expensive products to no avail, and I have tried so many different things. I have been using nixoderm for approximately three weeks now and I am astonished with the results. I started using it in the midst of a really horrible breakout and it didn't so much help clear it up because the damage was already done,  but it really helped with the marks that remain afterward. I have still had some small pimples but they come to a head quickly and go away quickly. I'm a picker so the fact that they come  to a head makes it easier to leave them alone once I can pop them. My pimples didn't come to a head before.  I use it only at night because it's a thick paste and just wouldn't work for daytime. It says to cut it with Vaseline if you have sensitive skin but I usually put on my night time moisturizer first and then blend someone nixoderm on top. I go a little heavier if i see there might be a pimple emerging. It does have a burning sensation but it subsides after about 10 minutes. It  causes something peeling, which I thought might just be from the glycolic acid peel I still use for dark spots , but a friend of mine tried nixoderm and says that she started peeling after a few days as well. I found an info sheet online that says use for 7 or 10 days then stop for 3. I have done so and I imagine it's just to give your skin a rest due to the exfoliating effect. I survived pms with no breakout whatsoever. The end result is my skin hasn't looked this amazing in years. I think it is even helping to fade my dark spots as well. I don't have a before picture to take, but I can tell you at any given time I would have 5-6 pimples that would stick around for at least a week at any given time. Highly highly recommend!!

column6: Twink Designs Metallic Temporary Tattoos, 4 Individual Sheets of Beautiful Tattoo Flash and Body Art
column14:
I received this product for free or highly discounted in exchange for an honest review.

I have tried a few different type of metallic tattoos. Some of them are great and others are not. Some of them last for a up to 2-3 weeks while a lot of only lasted a couple days. I am happy to say these tattoos go into the good pile. My sister and I love metallic tattoos, so we both tried them out, and we both love them. They are easy to put on, and they lasted our entire two week vacation at out summer home. When we got home, we did have to take them off for work, and they came off easy as well. What we did was rub in some baby-oil and let it soak in and then hopped into the shower and scrub it off. It doesn't take a lot of scrubbing; the oil and the steam from the shower do the work for you.

The quality of the tattoos were great, and the quantity was good. There were two sheets and each sheet had about a dozen tattoos, and there were a variety of designs. My sister loved all the arrows while I favored the birds. We were both happy with the selection and did not feel limited in our choices. These are great for vacation time especially when you do not want to bring jewelry with you. They lasted a long time even through sweaty days, swimming (in fresh water,) the sand, and showering (without baby-oil.) They are just fun things to have, and we did have a blast using them and got more than a few compliments while wearing them. I would definitely buy these again next summer.

Overall, we both recommend this product.

column6: Salon Shampoo Bowl Unit Neck Gel Rest SA-01
column13: I like the gel rests the best because they are the ...
column14:
This rest solves the gel rest problem. I like the gel rests the best because they are the most comfortable and durable. I can sanitize them better than any other rests I've used. The problems I've had with most of the gel neck rests, is they are only good until they get wet, then they slip off. I've tried the gel rests with the built in suction cups before. They are better than the ones without, but they eventually give way when wet as well. The major pro with this item is the suction cups are made of material that are not gel. They adhere terrifically. They are built around the gel and attached that way. I'm assuming one would want to keep that area dry in between uses so it doesn't eventually break down there.
The only problem I have is the single cup does not reach to the outside under the sink. Not sure if my sink has too thick of a rest? Either way, it is not made for universal use. Nevertheless, it still stays on, the single one just stays un attached. It does get caught on the chair sometimes if I am not careful when I bring the client up from the bowl. If this company would make this rest a little longer in the single cup area, it would fit most sinks, and I would sing their praises and look for a way to rate it with 10 stars!

column13: Creates a sticky feel to my hair..
column14:
I wish this product, or any Dove product, worked out for me because they have some really dreamy scents!

After the first wash, everything was fine. I wash my hair everyday, so the second day I started to feel my hair less clean and more stiff. On the third day, my hair looked greasy. On the fourth day, my hair looked greasy and I could barely get a comb through it.

This was experimented on my hair on days where no other products were used in my hair. This leads me to believe that this shampoo and conditioner duo, like all Dove shampoos and conditioners do to me, left product build up within my tresses.

Not a good look, but to each their own. I personally like the results of a clarifying shampoo and a heavy conditioner combo of Garnier and Herbal Essence. Works wonders for me, but definitely not Dove.

column6: Haircut Cape Kids, Worry Free Goodie Umbrella Catcher Apron Hairdresser Barber Hair Stylist
column14:
Haircuts can be a huge mess if your cutting hair at home. My kids and even the hubby hates to have hair all over them after a hair cut. The broom never seems to pick all the hair up and we still seem to find hair days later. I have always wanted to try a haircut cape to see if it would control the mess and I was so happy that it did. And Guess What??? Guys can use it when shaving their beards also, or if you trim their beards for them! I opened the package and it popped open for me, so quick and easy. My hubby wanted to try it first because he shaves every week and my bathroom always looks like a disaster afterwards. I placed the cape over his head and then velcroed the back securely. He shaved, un-velcroed the cape, slid the cape up and dumped all the hair in the trash. He went to the bath tub and just let the water rinse the leftover hair off. We hung up on the counter to let it air dry before folding up again. He was so happy that he didnt have to change clothes or sweep because they cape caught all the hair. Cant wait to try it on my little mans hair when it gets long again. He is going to love not being covered in hair.

*I recieved this Haircut Cape for Kids for a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased review

column14:
I'm kind of a newbie when it comes to essential oils, but my lady and all our friends are seriously into them and, intentionally or not, they've dragged me into it too. And I kind of like it, if truth be told. I feel a proper witch, brewing and blending, devising the proper blends to cure this or that ailment. This, however, is the very first cream I saw infused with essential oils, but since I am very familiar with Plant Therapy brand products, I had every confidence that they would deliver a quality product and so I went ahead and ordered.

I really enjoy this. Now, the listing says "aromatherapy" but I'm a dude who can't smell for beans. No sense of smell unless it's a steam-roller in-your-face Hulk-strong scent. So I never quite know if I am able to benefit fully from these types of things. But whoa-oh-oh! I used this and, sense of smell or not, I was awake! My skin felt tingly and alive. I felt quite energised and refreshed (and the lady said I smelled divine). It comes in a nice bottle, professional and comprehensive labeling. column13: Axe 3-in-1 shampoo/conditioner/body wash is just as expected
column14:
The biggest benefit of this product is you have just one container to manage. If you are going to use the gym/pool shower, it is a hassle to carry multiple bottles.

The bottle itself is big and contains 22 oz of product whereas standard size bottles contain only 14 oz. It makes sense for this product to be big because you use much more of the stuff per shower.

I am satisfied with this product. It lathers well and smells nice, excellent for use after exercise. The shampoo and body wash aspect of it works very well, but the conditioner is not the same as traditional oil-based conditioners. I am accustomed to conditioners that use oils to make my hair smoother and easy to comb, but this conditioner doesn't seem to have that effect. I was expecting this, since most shampoo+conditioner combinations don't feel the same as traditional conditioners. If you have very dry or brittle hair, you may need to use a dedicated conditioner in addition to this product. Overall though, it is a great 3-in-1 product for the average person.

column6: Roux Anti Aging Ampolletas, 619 Extra Moisture, 3 Count
column14:
This product works wonders on my hair! I am natural 4c- extremely dry, kinky and fragile. I purchased this product from my local Sallyâ€™s. Thankfully the sales clerk was very good and encouraged me to take advantage of the sale. This product normally sells for round 9 regular price. I think I got maybe 4 boxes for less than 20 during the sale. I choose to write a review on Amazon because I do enjoy shopping the site and I really depend on reviews when making purchases here or elsewhere.

I have been natural since 2008. After many years of frustration with breakage and difficult to manage hair, I returned to relaxer around April 2011. After on application my hair literally fell out! By June of 2011 I was down to hair that barely covered my scalp. Starting over natural I struggled with the same frustrations as before. Since relaxers were no longer an option I resigned to wearing wigs and just focus on keeping my hair healthy and clean. I've now been using 619 for at least 4 months. I noticed a difference in the state of my hair after the first use. It was noticeably softer and more manageable. After 4 months my hair is stronger, way less breakage, moist, maintaining length, and is way softer than it has ever been! Even my hair coils also seem to be more relaxed and not as tight. It seems that the stronger my hair gets, the less it coils. I do not have nearly as much shrinkage after shampooing. Because it has been difficult to restore moisture after shampooing, I try to go at least 2 weeks before shampooing. This not so much an issue with 619; however, I do not care to shampoo too often. I did not want to wait 2 weeks between 619 treatments. I apply it to my hair a couple times a week. Since my hair is short, I do not need to use a full bottle. I pour 619 into a small spray bottle. This is a great way to store leftover and makes it much easier to apply evenly.

Although this product is a bit expensive, it is worth the money! I would encourage you to check out Sallyâ€™s and try to catch it on sale.ncourage you to check out Sallyâ€™s and try to catch it on sale.

column14:
Wow, I have to say this rosewater is fantastic!

I live in Houston, Texas- a place infamous for scorching summers and finicky weather- and through all the humidity and heat waves this has given my skin a little bit of sanctuary. I was skeptical at first but over the past several days I've noticed that my skin looks a lot clearer as well as more even and youthful (I'm only 21, but hey late nights get to you either way).
Generally my skin is OK (some old acne scars here and there, and a couple of small bumps) but since I've started using this 1x in the morning, and then 1x in the evening I've noticed that my skin has started to have a nice glow to it.. I've also started using facial sunscreen recently and so far my efforts have proved to be effective- even a random lady at a bus stop commented on my complexion "You have such beautiful skin, like a baby!" Not only that but it smells lovely- like freshly cut roses :)

I am thrilled :) I'm definitely going to be buying another bottle at this rate- only downside is the price, and the fact that the product goes pretty quickly when used with regular cotton rounds and quarter sized amount.

column14: I'm old and have used a lot of electric shavers. In all cases I have found that the electric shavers and their blades do an okay job of cutting facial hair. It's not as close as a blade, but "close enough" so your face looks smooth. These Braun replacement blades/screen last about a year. Cleaning the shaver in the cleaning solution prolongs the screen and the blade's life. The solution, however, is expensive. The newer electric shavers can be rinsed clean just using tap water, and they shave is just as close as the Braun. I have since moved on from the Braun because of the expense of cleaning solution (which is nothing more than rubbing alcohol and a tiny bit of mineral oil and a couple of drops of lemon extract). One star deducted because of the price of the cleaning solution.

column14:
I am a fan of essential oils and i really like lemon oil for cleaning my house as i have children and don't like exposing them to chemicals. I have a 32 oz spray bottle and i mix about 80 drops of lemon oil and about 40 drops of tea tree oil and distilled water. I just spray on my counters to clean them. You can pretty much use it anywhere; toilet seats, laundry for a fresh scent.
Another use that I always talk to my friends about is using it for bad breath and to whiten teeth a bit. I'm a dental hygienist and i will mix a few drops with a little baking soda and coconut oil and apply it to my teeth, after brushing, and let it sit for a while and it helps whiten my teeth a bit as i love coffee but i don't love that coffee stains my teeth.
This particular brand, morning pep, i had never heard of until recently and I had been ordering from the popular brands that cost and arm and a leg. This works just as well, has a great scent and it isn't diluted and there are no additives or chemicals that i don't want. The seller even wrapped the bottle really well in bubble wrap to prevent any leakage or breaking of the bottle. I did receive a discount to test it out and this is my opinion of this lemon oil that is not at all swayed by the fact i bought this at a discount. Overall, I'm pleased with morning pep's lemon oil and it works just as well as the popular brands but doesn't cost an arm and a leg. I have been paying way too much for years and am pleased that i can order this here on amazon and get a quality oil that doesn't kill my wallet. I would recommend this.

column6: L'Oreal Paris Voluminous Million Lashes Mascara, 0.3-Fluid Ounce
column14:
This is the only mascara that I will ever use. I love it!
Thankfully, I was blessed by God and my parents with lucious lashes of my own, but they aren't really dark... at all.

This mascara gives me the best look that I've come across when it comes to mascaras. I've tried pretty much all of the drugstore brands and nothing comes close to this.

It goes on easy and the brush really separates my lashes so I don't have to sit there and pay so much attention to detail.

It also doesn't remove easy for me, which I like. I cry, it doesn't budge. I go swimming, it doesn't budge. I sleep, it only slightly budges, but it's not good to sleep with makeup on anyway.

I love that I can apply 1 coat for an everyday look, and 2 coats for a more dramatic look. The photos show only 1 coat.

It does respond well to makeup remover wipes. Only then, depending on if you're using a quality brand, does the mascara remove with ease.

I simply adore the effects and will continue to purchase.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: My \newest\" one was a BrAun series 1 which I have used for years and loved. But when I recieved my new Series 9 ..."
column14:
I have been using my new razor for a week and a half now and here is what I think about the newest in BrAun's product line, the Series 9 9090cc. I have used regular straight edge razors, (cheaper ones and the more expensive kind) and several different electric razors in my life. My "newest" one was a BrAun series 1 which I have used for years and loved. But when I recieved my new Series 9 9090cc I could not wait to try it out. Unfortunately I had to wait since I had just shaved prior to recieving the package, aghh! The series 9 gives me a perfect, tight shave. It gets all of my facial hairs, no matter what direction they are growing in or what lenght they are. Those are issues I have always had with other electrics, not with the series 9. I do not get finger numbness from prolonged use and vibration, since I can shave much quicker now than before, and the vibration of the shaver is incredibly much more subtle, more like a massage. Three different, wide shave heads get all types of hair in one or two passes, and they move independently to the contours of your face . The battery charges in about an hour,has a niffty LED display to show me it's charge and you can charge it in an emergency in only five minutes, though I have not have had to do this yet even after a week of use. It comes with a carrying pouch and a cleaning brush that you will probably never ever need to use, since it includes a cleaning station that cleans and sanitizes the razor thoroughly after every use, and it also dries the blades with a built in fan. The trimmer works great, and I especially like it's new back facing mount, which makes it easier to get those pesky sideburns and mustaches into proper shape. It has a special power lock function which keeps it from being turned on by accidentally pushing the power button, which is great for when you travel. I even love it's chrome and satin black look, it' like it was made for the terminator :) . I can Honestly say, just as about any other guy out there who has to shave constantly, that I have never looked forward to the daily grind of having to shave. Until now. This is hands down, the best shaving experience I have ever had, period. In my opinion, there are only three "downsides" to this shaver. I find that many times as I shave, I inadvertently flip up the swivel head button because of it's placement. Also the cleaning solution is not exactly inexpensive and you will need to replace it about every eight weeks. Finally, it's about a $300 investment, that will hopefully will come down with time.
To sum it all up: Pros== EVERYTHING, close shave, fast, beautiful, cleaning station, multiple wide heads, long battery life, battery power indicator, power lock travel function. Cons- in reality, just the price tag about $300, and you will have to spend a little for the comfort of always having a fresh, clean shave using the cleaning solution, not a bad trade I believe.
Finally I want to say that even though I have recieved the product as a special promotion from Braun, my review has been as thorough and honest as I could have possibly have made it.

Update:

After having used the shaver for almost three weeks now, I still have to say that is hands down the best electric shaver I have ever used. It cleans itself, four different shaver heads get to all my facial hairs, it's so fast that it's like getting a mini massage as you shave, it's ergonomic and overall a beautiful product. The only cons to this product that I have been able to ascertain: it's not cheap, at over $300, but this is a treat for your face, so not necessarily a con if you hate shaving; you will have to spend some money periodically to replace the cleaning cartridges, but again, the flip side is using a newly cleaned shaver every time. The biggest drawback for me, is the multi-head lock switch and pivoting head: the switch is placed exactly where I place my thumb while shaving, so I have to be extra careful not to push on it while shaving or I inadvertently release the head. Also the head of the shaver, I find if I press just a little too much and not even that strongly, it releases from the lock and pivots by itself as I shave. This last point might be the big issue for me. Will the head assembly eventually fail because it can't remain easily locked while shaving? That is the big question, and considering what you will have to pay for this product, it is THE big question in my mind. I give it a 4.5 out of 5 just because of the shaver head locking issue and nothing else. Overall still love this shavershaving or I inadvertently release the head. Also the head of the shaver, I find if I press just a little too much and not even that strongly, it releases from the lock and pivots by itself as I shave. This last point might be the big issue for me. Will the head assembly eventually fail because it can't remain easily locked while shaving? That is the big question, and considering what you will have to pay for this product, it is THE big question in my mind. I give it a 4.5 out of 5 just because of the shaver head locking issue and nothing else. Overall still love this shaver

column6: ARM & HAMMER Truly Radiant Battery Toothbrush + Toothpaste Pack
column13: Big improvement over manual brush, A step below Sonicare
column14:
Spinbrush Truly Radiant's Regimen Pack is Arm & Hammer's entry into the mid-priced powered toothbrush market. It is a step below Sonicare, but also far more affordable the the premier electric brushes. Spinbrush is battery-powered (included and installed) and offer above-average cleaning capability at the touch of a button. What's missing relative to the higher end alternatives is a timer. You can brush for 2 minutes, 5 minutes, or 10 and never know. Until you press off, it will continue running. The timed brush feature is standard fare for Oral B and Sonicare's electric line. This kit comes with two powered two brushes each with a replacement brush head. There's also a 4.3 oz Arm & Hammer toothpaste, though it doesn't matter much what toothpaste is used unless you have particular dental issues (sensitive gums, enamel decay, etc.). The brush head consists of a a spinning spherical brush on top and an oblong bottom that goes back and forth. This is excellent for removing plaque and getting a deeper clean than a manual brush could offer. One concern that may affect some users is that the motor on this brush is very loud, making it difficult to brush and watch TV at the same time. It's loud enough that it might wake up your spouse if they're still asleep while you're brushing. It would also be nice to have a cap to cover the brush head when not in use. Despite this, Arm & Hammer's Spinbrush offers practical way to improve your dental hygiene. 4/5 stars.

UPDATE: As of 10/14/15, my wife's Spinbrush stopped working abruptly. Mine is still working, but the battery is only half as powerful as it originally was. This powered toothbrush is not a long-term solution. It will last about 6-8 weeks with regular usage. For those who want a long-term solution, invest upmarket to Sonicare or Oral B's more robust electric toothbrush options.

column6: Jergens Natural Glow Instant Sun Sunless Tanning Mousse
column13: Good if you know how to use it
column14:
I've been using this all summer and it has worked well for me. I've had several pre-cancerous moles removed so I'm careful to stay out of the sun but I still like to look normal aka not blinding white. My friends noticed after I started using this product that I looked tanner but they said it looked very natural and a few of them went out and bought it for themselves. The first time I applied this I used my hands and it was streaky and left my hands stained. Ever since then I have applied it with a tanning mitt and it has been perfect. I usually exfoliate once a week (with scrub AND an abrasive glove) especially on my ankles and knees, no lotion, then apply this when my skin is dry. I do another layer every few days until I can tell it's starting to get blotchy in some areas and then I start over with exfoliating.

For my purposes of looking natural and not like a bronzed goddess this method has worked well for me and it's become my favorite tanner. If you sweat a lot or shave every day obviously it's going to come off sooner because you're exfoliating the skin it has affected. And while it "dries" in 60 seconds you have to use your own common sense and know that it takes a few hours to really "set in" and going out to play tennis or anything where you sweat a lot right after you use tanner is a bad idea.

column6: Christian Dior Diorshow Maximizer Lash Plumping Serum 10ml/0.33oz
column14: This primer works pretty well.  It gives me additional volume and fattens my lashes nicely.  Be sure and wait until it's dry before applying regular black mascara.  I use a regular mascara for the first coat and a waterproof formula for the last coat (to ensure my lashes hold the curl).  This method works really well for me.  I'm not sure that this primer works better than drugstore primers, because I haven't tried any of the drugstore brands, but I do know that my lashes look fuller and thicker when I use the Dior product.  Some people have suggested that this primer is simply a white mascara but if you look closely, there are little fibers in it that enable it to add dimension and heft to the lashes.  I'm not sure I would repurchase this product though.  Although I haven't tried it, it's possible that I would get the same false lash effect with a few more coats of regular black mascara.  I guess I can try this on one eye to see whether it makes a difference.  However, I do know that I like the way my lashes look when I use this primer.  Who knows?, it may grow on me.  I do recommend it if you have thin sparse lashes.  It definitely adds weight and volume for a fuller, thicker look.  And my lashes stay nice and soft to boot.

column13: Great palette for a great price!!
column14:
I'm a huge fan of Disney, and Elsa is a character I heavily relate to, so seeing a beauty book of her I was sold! I love this palette! There are 8 shadows, a highlighter, 2 eyeliners, an eyeshadow brush, and a lip color (kind of a liquid lipstick) and for $12 (Walgreen's price) its totally worth it!
The eyeshadow are so nice! Love the pigmentation and texture! Very soft and nice! I only had one dud and that was the color called "Elsa" which is the purple color. That shadow is pretty bad. Not pigmented and pretty much had hardpan when I bought it. Which sucks. But the other colors do make up for it!
The highlighter is my personal favorite thing from this beauty book! It's such a nice texture and is very shimmery! It's a very intense highlight but if you tap off the brush its very nice and subtle-ish ðŸ˜‰ lasts all day and look stunning on the face!
The eyeliners are okay as well! Not incredible, but not awful! One does have shimmer so, be cautious if you want to wear it in the waterline (I would assume it would be fine, just be aware of the glitter in it! ðŸ’–)
The brush is awesome! I use it for both packing on eyeshadows and blending! I've washed it around 3 times since I've gotten it and have had no shedding! Very soft as well!
The lip color is a mix between a lip gloss and a liquid lipstick. Very pigmented and has a great texure, but it doesn't dry matte and has a bit of shine. I love it! Not sure of the staying power though! I think it lasted maybe 1-2 hours? Which isn't bad but not something I'd necessarily reach for if I'm going out for longer than that.
Overall id give this palette a 4.5 stars. Only because the Elsa shadow is a very bad shadow and you'd assume that would be the stand out shade. But I would highly recommend for anyone who likes Disney, Frozen, and Makeup! ðŸ’–ðŸ’–ðŸ’–

column6: xtava Allure 2200W Professional Ionic Ceramic Hair Dryer - Bring the Salon to Your Home with This Powerful and Precise Blow Dryer - 2 Speeds - 3 Heat Settings (Ebony)
column14: Needed a new dryer and have been shopping around for a while.  I've looked at this one online a few times but couldn't justify the price.  Then it  went on sale and I jumped on it.  Just got it, first use.  It's not silver, like the one pictured, but I didn't buy it for color so I don't care (mine is kind of a gunmetal black).  Beautifully packaged, easy to understand directions/ switches (and they should be- I'm drying my hair, not launching a rocket into space).  A bit heavier than my last dryer, but not uncomfortable.  I did notice a really mild chemical odor, but I was using the dryer on its highest setting and I'm guessing it had to do with the casing heating up.  The odor did go away and it was never overpowering and didn't make me think the dryer was going to explode in my hand or anything.  The dryer did NOT dry my thick, mid-back length hair in 5 minutes (as was claimed by another reviewer, I think) but it did SIGNIFICANTLY decrease my drying time.  Took about 22 minutes down from 40-50 (and would still have damp spots), and that was with a little extra time fiddling around styling because.....MY HAIR LOOKS AWESOME.  Seriously.  I could be in a hair products commercial right now, I'm not kidding.  I feel like my gorgeous hair is going to waste just sitting inside writing an Amazon review, but this baby deserves it so I sat right down to do it.  I would have NEVER believed a dryer would make so much difference (otherwise I'd have bought this ages ago), but truly, I look like I just walked out of the salon.  I want to stockpile these so I never have to live without it.  This was a phenomenal deal on sale, but I would pay full price (and then some) knowing what I know now.

column6: DHC Q10 CreamII(SS) 20gx1
column14:
A consummate knock-off of DHC's Coenzyme Q10 moisturizing cream.

If you're looking to save money on the coveted product, don't bother with this. The jar looks legit, and maybe it is (just the jar though), but the cream absolutely will not do anything for wrinkles or fine lines the way the real DHC product does.

I've been using this cream for a month and it's done nothing for fine lines. When I used the tiny free sample that the real DHC sent me in the mail, I saw a noticeable visible improvement in the fine lines around my eyes and mouth within only 3 days.

Save your time and money and just buy directly from DHC, seriously. This stuff doesn't even smell like the real thing because it's lacking the ingredient that diminishes the appearance of wrinkles.

I gave this product 2 stars for "I don't like it" instead of 1 star for "I hate it" because at the very least I can still use it as a very basic moisturizer.

Spend your money patronizing businesses that actually give you a high-quality product that works instead of individuals who are just looking to make a quick buck ripping you off.

column6: InstaNatural Organic Rosehip Seed Oil - 100% Pure & Unrefined Virgin Oil - Natural Moisturizer for Face, Skin, Hair, Stretch Marks, Scars, Wrinkles & Fine Lines - Omega 6, Vitamin A & C - 4 Oz
column13: Linoleic Acid for Acne Prone guys and gals
column14:
I'm currently making the transition into using more natural beauty products in my nightly routine to encourage healthy cell growth and keep wrinkles at bay. I may only be 21, but I've come to fully understand that prevention is key!

Anyways, the sizing of this bottle is very generous for the price, the bottle came packaged well and sealed properly. 1 star there.
The smell was fine- it smelled slightly of roses and oil, as I fully expected- not rancid (thankfully). I'm not in love with the smell but it smells as it should. +1 star.
I'm happy to note that the product does not irritate my acne prone skin, nor does it cause break outs- it absorbs into my skin quickly and goes on very lightly (yay!). It's still an oil so I wouldn't recommend applying it in the morning, but it works wonderfully as a night-time wrinkle/moisturizing treatment. (especially around the eyes)

That being said it is advised to those who have moderate/severe acne to avoid direct application to trouble areas, but rosehip seed oil has a higher percentage of Linoleic acid (44%) compared to Oleic acid (14%) which is richer and more likely to cause problems for those with acne. I don't apply this oil to my trouble areas on the sides of my forehead, but I've been applying it to minor trouble areas on the sides of my cheeks (note: MINOR) and haven't experienced any breakouts. 2 more stars right there baby.

Overall this product is pretty great, hasn't caused me any problems yet (which is saying a lot because I have sensitive skin prone to breakouts)- but I haven't seen any results either so until then I'll leave off the 1 star. When I do notice any changes I'll be sure to come back and revise this :)

P.S. if you have acne prone skin I highly suggest doing some research into Linoleic vs Oleic acids- skin is very delicate and should be taken care of properly with the proper products for your skin type :)

We have a 40ish male, with thicker facial hair and a 20ish year old with much less, finer facial hair. The shaver wasn't something the 40ish year old liked. He said the shaver did not allow for a close shave that he prefers. He complained it didn't get as close to hard to get places, around the nose. But he did say this is why he never uses electric shavers, this is no different. Now, the 20ish year old loved it. He said he thought it shaved close and was easy to handle even for his large hands. The shave was close for him and it allowed him to shave in a hurry.

My thought is the hair on my husband is too thick, and there is too much for this shaver and my sons hair is thinner and easier to shave for this "economical" priced shaver. I think my husband would need a heavier duty shaver for him to be happier.

column13: The ones they're selling in Bloomingdales is fake!!!
column14: Best smelling perfume on earth ðŸ˜³ This perfume was made for me ðŸ˜³After smelling this I fell head over heels jack&rose titanic type of love with this. after smelling this perfume other perfumes/colognes were like a joke to me. This is my second bottle. The first I stole from my sister lol she is a perfume/cologne junkie When my first bottle finished I went to Bloomingdales to get a new one, took it home and realized the one in the new box didn't smell the same. And it was pink. The original was a very light wash of yellow I took it back and told them it smelled different. They said they both smell the same to them. The thing is they had the real deal on display and was selling the fake ones. I told them I was willing to get the one display even tho it was used up but you know they said no ðŸ˜ They then blindfolded me in the store lol they had me smell the one on display then made me smell coffee beans then made me smell the one in the box. They were so surprised I could tell the difference lol I personally think the ones in the store that are refillable smells so fruity and fake. I've become a Thierry Mugler womanity insanity lol I know my baby. When purchasing this I was so scared but when I got it was so happy to be reunited with the real deal. Whenever I wear this I get at least 5 compliments a day of how good I smell. When I wore the one I purchased from Bloomingdales I got none. That was another reason I knew it wasn't the same.  Womanity just how that sounds. I have a lot of perfumes and colognes and I'm looking at them like what a waste of money. I have brands like Hermes Givenchy Versace Balenciaga Prada Bvlgari Hanae and a whole lot more but none of those top my baby Thierry. It's also the best sent for winter. The oil is on the greasier side so is best applied at night. The smell is strong but not to bothering at all. You get used to it after some time. This oil acts as a conditioner for my face. In the morning I can't avoid touching my face because after many years my face feels smooth and nourished. I will update my review after a couple months if I see any major change in my scars which I am sincerely hoping will diminish with it.

My face and alcohol don't get along, and applying this is like dousing my face in a martini. It smells very alcoholic and has that tell-tail "cooling" effect that alcohol has (plus alcohol is listed right there at the top of the ingredients list). Alcohol is drying and causes faster aging, and unfortunately it is the first or second ingredient in a lot of beauty products. Besides this, it is really a great sunscreen. It doesn't wear off and creates a nice makeup base. It's non-shiney and doesn't cause breakouts for me at least. But I do feel that it's somewhat drying especially around my eyes, which is why I'll keep looking for the perfect sunscreen.

column6: Braun Silk-Ã©pil 7 Wet and Dry Epilator, White
column14:
Thanks Braun and Bzzagent for allowing me to review this product! I couldn't wait to try out this epilator as I was in desperate need of an upgrade from my old epilator. For those who are not familiar with epilators, the Braun series 7 epilator is one of Braun's more expensive products that has added features to make sure that the device is relatively easy and painless to use. The massaging cap and built in light make it so much easier to spot tiny hairs and epilate without too much pain. This product has two speed settings and several attachment heads that can be used depending on the area that needs to be epilated. I would recommend using the lowest setting on areas like the legs or arms, where there is generally thicker hair and more hair growth. In this way, the epilator can grab the hair from the root without breakage. So far, I have only used the sensitive area cap and the shaver cap. The razor is wonderful; you could just use this product for the razor attachment to be honest. I have never had a smoother shave! The sensitive area cap is not as effective at grabbing hairs compared to the regular epilator without a cap. I actually preferred not using a cap for my legs and bikini area. The charge lasts a fairly long time with this epilator. After plugging it into the outlet, it had full charge within an hour. After doing both my legs and armpits (approx. 40 minutes) , it was still working which was great! Overall, I am really impressed with this product! It is easy enough to use for beginners, but also advanced enough with multiple features that long time users can also enjoy it.

Tips and Tricks for People New to Epilating:
- Epilating for the first time will definitely be painful, but I promise the pain will lessen after a few uses! Try numbing cream or taking a painkiller 30 minutes before epilating if you have a very low pain threshold.
-Exfoliate, exfoliate, exfoliate! Exfoliate with a good scrub before and after epilating to prevent ingrown hairs. This is so important. Unless you want to manually pluck every in grown hair out, you need to exfoliate.
-Use aloe vera gel or another type of soothing ointment after epilating. It can really calm down the redness and irritation that happens after epilation.
-Applying baby powder onto the areas that you are about to epilate can help dry up any excess water or residue that is left on the skin. It's easier for the device to grab dry hairs vs wet hairs.
-Make sure that your hair is the correct length before epilating. I think the optimal length is 2mm-5mm. When the hairs are too long, their is a lot of breakage and left over stubble, which defeats the purpose of using an epilator haha.

column14: This stuff actually works! I have naturally dark brown hair and I have been highlighting it (with bleach, done professionally) to blonde for about a year now. My friends notice the difference and it is obvious in pictures. I use a regular shampoo first, then I let this shampoo sit on my hair for five minutes then rinse it out and put more on for another five minutes. For the conditioner, I mix it in with a regular conditioner and let it sit for 2-3 minutes. The only drawback to these products is that they dry out your hair, so if you notice your hair dried out or breaking, I recommend using a hydrating shampoo to go along with this.

column6: Brights Semi Permanent Hair Color
column13: I didn't dilute it with water or anything like some other users on here have done
column14: I've always wanted to try a pastel color, but have never taken the plunge, partially because I've been coloring my hair for 15 years (mostly darker brunette shades). My hair has always pulled red mind you, no matter if I use ash based color or neutral. After buzzing my hair 5 months ago, I decided to finally do something different once it grew out to a normal length. I bleached my natural hair color for 45 minutes with Keleidoscope Blue bleach from Sally's with 30 volume developer for 45 minutes. My hair came out a yellow tone on the roots, with orange on the tips. Which is natural for me when bleaching my hair. I decided to do a the smokey pink permanent hair color from Sally's just to see what it would it do. It was awful. My hair was still orange and added no pink whatsoever. That's when turned to "Shark Blue". I slapped it onto my "orange" hair with a processing cap and let it sit for an hour and a half. I didn't dilute it with water or anything like some other users on here have done. I did occasionally put my hair dryer on it to give it some heat. Once I rinsed it in cool water it came out a grey/blue color which I'm obsessed with. I plan on getting violet shampoo and not washing it for a couple days at a time to maintain the color. But needless to say I'm very pleased.

column13: Better than you ever could expect

Received these as a gift. Didn't expect much but I was horribly wrong! They work better than anything I've ever used. No more messy oily makeup remover. No more filling the landfills with disposable wipes that hardly work.

These require minimal effort and get everything off. I dampen the towel, apply my facial cleaner and gently wipe all my makeup off in mere minutes. Rinse the wipe with mild hand soap to remove the makeup residue, wring and hang dry for the next use. They are machine washable just don't use fabric softener or dry sheets. I have accidentally included them in a load where I used fabric softener and it did not effect their effectiveness. I do try to avoid it though as long term used of fabric softener does build up residue in fabrics especially microfiber.

They are cheaper in Wal-Mart so do a little looking around or if you don't have time buy them here, they are worth every penny!

column13: ... just over a year ago and was initially very happy with the functioning until it quit working altogether!
column14: I purchased the mirage diffuser just over a year ago and was initially very happy with the functioning, but less than 6 months later, the misting action was barely working and unit shuts off before the oil has been diffused.  I use high quality essential oils and have tried cleaning it after each use with vinegar/water solution. Unit will work slightly better for a brief time (a few minutes) and then quits. I have contacted ZAQ 4 times and they have not responded. I am very disappointed with ZAQs customer service.  While having difficulty with the Mirage, I purchased the ZAQ Allay, the Paradise and the Lotus models and they all put out MUCH more plume/mist and so far they continue working until all oil/water has been diffused, however, I have only had them 2-3 months, so we'll see if they last. I love ZAQ diffusers, while they work, but may need to plan to replace them every 6 months to a year.  It's unfortunate that  ZAQ does not stand behind their products and at the very least respond to emails.

column6: Braun Silk-Ã©pil 9 9-521 Women's Epilator, Electric Hair Removal, Cordless, Wet & Dry, White/Pink
column14:
This is the first epilator I've ever purchased/used, so I don't have a comparison to make with another type/brand.

It came charged, which was very nice. The first use was insanely painful. Akin to waxing. I had to take pain breaks. But the following uses are less painful.

This DOES NOT capture every hair. I still had to use tweezers to remove hair here and there. Does not prevent ingrown hairs. (Other reviews have said they don't get ingrown hairs from this.) And it needs to be cleaned between legs. Hair gets caught in and under the head. But it comes with a little brush, and it's very easy to sweep away the hair.

I'm actually happy with it. It is much easier/less messy than waxing. And seems like hair does take longer to come back even compared to waxing. Fast-charging. And it's pinky and sparkly, which if you're a girly-girl, that's fun.

column6: Baiden Tan Mitten - Pre-Tan Scrub Exfoliator for Face & Body, Use With Self-Tanning Lotion & Spray, Super Effective Fake-Tanner Remover, Enhances All Forms Of Tanning: Spray, Self, Sun & Bed
column13: I did notice my legs got a nice tan 2-3 days into it
column14:
I'm a filipino and hispanic male, both these races can be fairly dark.

Growing up I was left in the sun with a tan on my arms and face, which is known as a farmers tan. I didn't wear shorts so my legs didn't get exposed to the sun that much, they're a different tone from my arms. This gives me my insecurity of wearing shorts.

Seeing how this says it removes tan, I thought I'd give it a try. My first time I did on my arms I noticed the dead skin rolling off, i also used it on my legs. When I went to go tan (covering my arms and wearing a hat), I did notice my legs got a nice tan 2-3 days into it.

When I use the mitten for the second time on my arms the dead skin rolled off, but the next day my arms barely looked lighter. It's true it gives you a nice tan, but i wouldn't recommend this to people with farmers tans. It also leaves your skin really smooth.
