column6: L'Oreal Paris Sublime Bronze Pro Perfect Salon Airbrush
column14:
I love this stuff. I tanned all through my youth and prefer to be a dark color, but now I am in my 30s and have become all too aware of the sun's effect and aging. Well, I find this to be a terrific solution. It's really not too dark but builds as dark as you want it to. In fact under my spray I am whiter than white. But a couple times a week I step in the tub and spray myself (I do it here because there's nothing to clean up- just turn the water on after you are done). Then usually after thirty minutes to an hour I spray my legs and arms again. I even spray my face during the first round. The second round probably isn't necessary for most but I like to keep myself nice and brown. Also I should add that this stuff is dry in just a few minutes and has hardly any "scent". I say scent because it's not a typical gross tanner smell.
I had a great realization how much better this stuff is the other day because I thought I could rub on some lotion the other day and succeed without any streaks or dark spots. Nope. I turned out horrible and had to scrub for days in the shower. Back to the spray for me. As long as you pay attention with even streaks you will be perfect.
I should also add that I use subscribe and save. I am never without a tan and I save money in the process.

column6: The Honest Company - Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30, 3 Fl Oz
column13: Buy if you want to look like Larry the Lobster
column14:
I agree with the majority of the posters here: steer clear of this product. My daughter breaks out in little bumps from "normal" sunscreen, so I too was excited when Costco offered a natural alternative in this Honest Company sunscreen.

After, spending the summer at the beach using Walmart sunscreen without any sunburns, my daughter had built up quite a base tan. Yesterday, we went to the beach and she used used Honest Co. for the first time. She came home with the most horrible sunburn ever! The rest of the family used Walmart brand sunscreen, and none of us burned - she was the only one, and she applied more than any of the rest of us (also, she is more olive toned than any of the rest of us). Therefore, the only problems came from this horrible sunscreen.

column13: Good product that has been working for me.
column14: I have been slowly thinning in the front since my early 30's (I'm 38 now) and was looking for a way to combat it. During my research I came across this product about 13 months ago. The reviews were mostly very positive, so I figured for the price it was worth giving it a shot. I was not looking to sprout tons of new hair or anything like that, but just to try and keep what I have as long as I can. I also wanted to wait before writing a review because you have to give hair loss products time to work.  I have not been using this shampoo for a little over 12 months now and I can happily say that it has done what I was hoping it would do, which is help me keep what I have. I have no noticeable hair loss in the last year, and in fact, my hair actually looks and feels thicker. I'm not sure if I have actually grown new hair or the shampoo has just made it look thicker, but I do know it looks better.  I got a haircut this morning and my stylist of 6 years told me that my hair looks and feels thicker than it has in several years, and that my scalp looks very healthy now. I use this every 2-3 days and leave it in 5-7 minutes while I shower. It lathers up very well, so you don't need to use a lot but you must make sure you massage it in very good as it needs to get in the hair follicles to be effective. I will update this review if anything changes for the positive or negative, but for now I'm very happy with this shampoo.

column6: ARM & HAMMER Truly Radiant Battery Toothbrush + Toothpaste Pack
column13: Good Entry Level Electric Toothbrush With Great Arm & Hammer Toothpaste
column14:
I've used the Arm & Hammer toothpaste with my electric toothbrush for several years and figured I'd give this electric toothbrush + toothpaste pack a try. I'll say right off the bat that if you're already using an electric toothbrush there's very little reason to switch to this kit unless you're looking for a cheaper replacement.

â–ºToothbrushes:
The toothbrushes in this kit use two AA batteries (included) that fit in the handle. The common theme with these types of electric brushes are that they're generally a bit larger and more noisy than the more refined (and expensive) brands like Oral B and Sonicare. That is very much the case here with the brushes in this kit. The other negative for me is that I felt the brushes were a bit too stiff; I already have a bad habit of brushing too hard so paired with these stiffer brushes I'm not doing my teeth any favors.

Each brush is considerably larger than both my Oral B and Sonicare brushes and features a multi-action head. I think they do a good enough job cleaning but again are considerably louder and offer a more jarring brushing experience.

â–ºTruly Radiant Toothpaste:
If you're familiar with Arm & Hammer toothpaste then you'll probably like the Truly Radiant formula. If you're not familiar with brushing with Arm & Hammer products then just be aware that these pastes feature baking soda as a primary ingredient. So your brushing experience will tend to be grittier than with other non-baking soda formulas. Personally the combination of baking soda and peroxide just leaves my teeth and mouth feeling cleaner than many of the other brands I've used in the past.

My everyday brand is Arm & Hammer Complete Care Plus Whitening and honestly I'm not able to tell a difference in the whiteness of my teeth after using the Truly Radiant brand. I may consider ordering more but that will likely mostly be determined by price.

â–ºIncluded in the Kit:
1) 2 Spinbrush toothbrushes
2) 4 AA batteries
3) 4 Toothbrush heads
4) 1 Truly Radiant toothpaste tube

â–ºClosing Comments:
I think this product is targeting two types of people: those that do not already own and electric toothbrush and those that are looking for a non-strip based whitening product. If you find yourself in either group this is probably not a bad purchase. Amazon's product page currently doesn't have a price (item is unavailable) but looking at other retailers this does seem to fit within the budget conscious market of electric toothbrushes. Overall a good experience. Recommended if your needs align to what the product does.brushes

column6: Yakusen Bath Roman ''Muddy White'' Japanese Bath Salts - 650g
column14:
Okay, I'm a huge fan of everything Japan and I've been wanting to go to an onsen for a long time, but because a trip to Japan isn't feasible at the moment I'd thought I'd give this a try instead (I know not the same, dream with me!!)

1.Smell: at first I was a tiny bit put off by the near-citsry floral smell (not a fan of citrus) but once in the water it melded into a very floral scent that actually comes off as calming- very nice. So the smell was not exactly the same straight out of the can (thank goodness)

2.Appearances: there's no doubt about it! This stuff will make your bath nice and white- it's like taking a milk bath :D (depending on how much you put it). At first the powder floats on the top, then sinks into a cloud of white and spans out into the water by itself. Very lovely.

3. Texture: This salt isn't grainy in the water at all :) it's not like putting epsom salt into the tub- like how you end up with irritating salt grains left over at the bottom. Nope, it's mostly powder like, a bit grainy in appearance but it blends into the water perfectly

4.Size: The size of the canister is pretty good- I was expecting a lot less but indeed it is a pretty good amount (and better be for $17!)

Overall I really like this product, I'm more than sure it will last me a long time :) Thank you Japan!

EDIT****************************************

I bought this bath powder again excited to be able to use it after a hiatus from baths- and while the seller was excellent and the item came well packaged and fast I realized that the formula for the product had changed. This new bath powder does NOT smell good. It smells really strong and almost manly. It burned my nostrils :(
Not only that but I could tell the formula had changed because the canister changed as well- rather than a regular finish- the canister was metallic- it had the same pattern but it's metallic red and orange. Don't get me wrong the change was beautiful- but the smell? awful. Very disappointed in the formula change. I'd post a picture but I gave this away to a friend as soon as I had drained the bath water- I wasn't even able to take my bath without my nose hurting.la change. He has experienced a healthier beard and softer skin in the days since he's been using both products.

It is a nice, gentle cleanser, and contains DMAE, Vitamin B5, and Retinol, along with several other ingredients including organic aloe leaf juice, organic olive oil, and organic lavender. The facial cleanser, like the beard oil, features a nozzle that dispenses oil pump by pump. This allows you to get what you need, without getting too much. It also prevents a mess, which I appreciate, since I am the one who has to clean the bathroom. *Smile*

column13: Rosacea coverage, Sunburn coverage, dark pigmentation coverage, HIGHLY recommend!
column14:
Rosacea coverage is my number one factor in foundation. This covers so well, and makes my face the entire same color. No break outs, no clogged pores, no scent. I wore no makeup to work one day and everyone asked if I was ok because my face was so red. Got a sunburn? Perfect coverage, no one will know! Now I know how to be able to go home sick!!! I also use the pressed powder to set my foundation because it is not a "wet" foundation that will dry into a matte. I do NOT use the applicator, seems to waste too much, I unscrew the lid with the applicator on it and just use a small squeeze per cheek and a little more for forehead coverage and I am all set to use the powder. Coverage lasts all day. I can come home and touch up my powder before going out and it looks all fresh again.
I HIGHLY recommend if you need it for flaw coverage. My daughter uses it to hide her acne scars. She is multi-racial and just uses the mineral wear powder/bronzer for darker tones.

column6: Konad Nail Art Stamping Polish, Black Pearl
column14:
Although Konad is great for my nail stamping plates, I think regular (super pigmented) black nail polish could do as well.

I do like that Konad black nail art stamping polish is thick enough to scrape well into the plates to get an almost-to-perfect even coat for a smooth transfer from plate to stamp to nails.

Pros:
-dries fairly quickly
-very pigmented/black
-thick (but not too thick)
-glossy
-good amount of product

Cons:
-pricier than regular black nail polish

Better than most regular black nail polishes, Konad nail art stamping plate gives a clear transfer (most of the time). Give it a try and see how you like it.

column6: Ossur Rebound Air Low Top Walker
column13: Aircast SP is better, but not by much
column14: This was the fourth (and last) walking boot that I had in three months. The Aircast SP was better, more comfortable and effective, but not by much. This boot is similar in design and appears to be better made, but has the same issues. The biggest complaint I have is that the plastic outer cover is supposed to go over the inflation and deflation bulbs that are built into the liner, but the smaller deflation bulb would slip under the cover and was constantly getting pressed by the cover as it shifted, thus deflating the air bladders and causing the boot to fit loosely. Also, the toe cap at the front seems like a good idea, but anything that gets in doesn't come out without removing the boot. After three weeks of use, the rubber that holds the plastic outer cover together had broken and the ankle strap was giving out. Still, this is a good boot. The liner is good, it's pretty comfy, and the bladder setup is very good when it was inflated. I just prefer the Aircast SP. It's more comfortable and the inflation setup is simpler and works.

column14: After reading all the reviews I had really hoped I would be able to use this hair dryer and skip the flat iron. Not happening. Also, the wattage is so low that I had to air dry my hair for nearly an hour first.Otherwise it would have taken me over half an hour to dry using the styler immediately after shampooing. That additional time for air drying is not always an option. My hair is chin length on the sides and very short in the back. Although my hair is quite thick it isn't long. This dryer does help remove some of the frizz, but I still need to use the flat iron to get rid of the "bulkiness" and smooth it. I think this dryer would be a great option for two of my friends who have thinner more layered hair. It would give them the curl and the volume without having to dry and then use the curling iron.

[[VIDEOID:980407e45e325083efa0c08247776d51]]This review is for the Sterling Silver Simulated Diamond Striped Eternity Ring.

This ring is the true definition of class! It is a standard eternity band lined with simulated diamonds for added class and sparkle. The banding is 360 degrees and runs the entirety of the band. The diamonds are just the right size. They add a little sparkle but not too much. It is very classy and elegant!

I think this ring would be great for a male or female. I actually love it to stack with other rings! It is not too blingy that it demands full attention so that is why it looks great paired with another ring! I own several rings from SilverCloseout and they all look great paired with it!

This ring comes boxed in a hard sided container and is set in black velvet for gift giving! It is truly beautiful! 5/5 stars for design, value and versatility.

[[VIDEOID:efd2705c5e995077eefbb580810e2284]]This review is for the Sterling Silver Cz Double Zig Zag Eternity Ring.

This ring is VERY fashionable! I have never seen a style like it! It is my favorite ring I own from SilverCloseout! The design looks even more incredible in person than in the photographs. The diamonds are two sizes. They dot the entirety of the banding and sparkle, sparkle, sparkle! I would say this ring is great for younger people as well as old! It is a very fashion forward style that looks great with all outfits!

The inside of the banding is smooth again my skin and doesn't cause irritation. SilverCloseout uses the highest quality silver so the metals feel great all day long and never tarnish or look old. I think this ring would be a great gift for a graduate, birthday or any other occasion! It does not look "romantic" but more "fun"! It is very girly!

This ring comes boxed in a hard sided box to keep it safe and it is great for gifting! You can wrap the box. Inside the ring is set in black velvet. 5/5 stars for value, design, and fun factor!

column6: AMIST Jewelry Stainless Steel Cross Bullet Pendant Necklace Chain Mens Silver
column13: Attractive Pendant; Chain Could be Stronger
column14:
Typically my family and I do not wear much jewelry. My wife wears the occasional necklace when weâ€™re going someplace that requires us to look nicer such as going our for a nice dinner, and she and I both wear wedding bands, but beyond that we donâ€™t really even think much about adornments like this. I have a teenage son, though, who saw this and thought he would enjoy it. So far he has been happy with it.

The first thing I noticed about this chain and pendant is the unique design of the pendant. It is in the shape of a bullet and has a cross on the middle of the bullet. This design makes it look fairly unique. It is also pretty heavy and the pendant is made very solid so it could be dropped from a very high distance, possibly three flights of stairs and not break or get ruined. The pendant is hollow too, so it can work as a container for holding glycerin tablets for those that need such.

The ring that holds the pendant to the chain appears to be substantial and strong. In the even that the whole should break it seems very unlikely that the ring would be the breaking point but instead the chain would be the likely point of failure. The chain is a typical ball link chain and is not the most strong available, which means it is also the inexpensive component in this set.

After looking over the design of the chain and pendant, I let my son try it and see how it fit him. Overall it fits pretty well, and though the chain does not have a clip, it appears to be able to fit almost anyone. (Of course, the chain could be carefully cut and a clip could be added without too much trouble.) This allows putting on this chain and pendant very easy as you do not have to hassle with a chainâ€™s clip. It also looks nice and has a unique appearance which my son likes. The bullet is also fairly realistic looking. Overall my son is very happy with how the chain and pendant looks and how it fits him.

Overall I am very happy with this chain and pendant. Though the chain is not especially strong, the design of the pendant is unique, the pendant is manufactured very well and will not break. Also this chain and pendant is easy to put on, looks nice and there is no hassle with a clip.

I have seen other necklaces similar to this one and have always wanted them, but they always turn out to be of a not so great quality.  This necklace comes in a lovely burgundy pouch which gives it a higher end feel. The necklace itself is sturdy and well made. The etching on the moon and the heart is perfect. There are no misspellings or scratches. The chain is high quality. I even gave it a few good tugs and it did not break. I love that there is a mixture of silver and gold on this as it would please lovers of both types of metals.  This is a very beautiful piece and I plan on buying more as gifts for upcoming holidays! column14:
Very beautiful piece. Arrived quickly and as pictured. I was more concerned with not being able to hold it before purchasing, but it feels good in the hand and serves the purpose it was created for.

The bead count is perfect and there are other great characteristics that aren't even highlighted in the product description. At the end of the main bead (guru, mother etc) there are two cords with three tiny beads each. These are useful if you are doing many repetitions and want to keep a further count of how many times you have made a complete circle. They slide up the cord and stay perfectly in place. Beautiful! Also, the color of the cord adds an authentic touch at a reasonable price.

column6:
Alex and Ani Bangle Bar Imitation Birthstone Bangle Bracelet, 7.75\" Jewelry 5 0 0 N Y Mothers day gift My wife loves these bracelets, and local stores seem to have limited selections, or are ridiculously overpriced. Birthstone bracelet makes great mother's day gift 2015-08-15 US 33107350 R37S24W9873W01 B00LEC2772 686891842 King Will TYRE Black Domed Tungsten Ring 8mm Brushed Matte Finished Wedding Band Size 7-14 Jewelry 5 2 3 N N Name's Black. Matte Black. Okay, first things first - the product image here is deceptive due to reflections on the polished edges of the ring. The image makes it look like the edges are silver-ish, but the ring is actually completely black. If you want a two-tone ring, this is not for you. If you want a black ring with polished edges and a brushed body, this is a great choice. (UPDATE: It looks like they've updated the photos to make the black edges more obvious - excellent.)

The brushed matte black main body looks just like the picture. I've tried both the polished black and brushed matte black versions of this ring, and they are both very comfortable - it just comes down to which look you prefer. All surfaces and edges are smooth and slide on/off my finger just great.

This ring has a classic shape in that it is a rounded design, much like gold wedding bands have been for many years. I happen to prefer King Will's beveled designs that have a flatter body because I think that they look better on my hands, but this is a very nice ring if you like the classic shape but want to move away from the age-old look of gold. I see more and more guys with black (or two-tone with black) wedding bands these days, so you don't have to feel like a total rebel getting this. :) For $20, it's hard to go wrong with this ring. It's very solidly constructed, like every King Will ring that I've ever tried.

As you likely already well know, tungsten carbide is not the same as pure tungsten. However, it is also much less expensive and has a lot of similar qualities - which is one reason why it is so popular for rings these days. What makes these rings so strong can also make them brittle, so rather than deforming like a gold band would if you hit it hard enough, these can crack. That's just a note, as you definitely don't have to baby these things.

Pros:
(*) Looks mostly like the product image except that the edges are black and not silver-ish like they appear in the photo
(*) Comfortable with very smooth surfaces everywhere

Cons:
(*) Absolutely none as long as you buy this knowing that the edges are black

column13: Don't pass up this super deal!
column14:
This is such a good deal, don't pass it up! First of all, you get 80 different types and colors of earrings for the price of one if you bought it at a different site or in store. I was a bit skeptical about the roughness that other reviewers mentioned. But, after looking at the earrings I couldn't see anything, nor do I feel anything. These earrings are a bit less flexible than what I'm used to, that's my only complaint though. I am also wearing it in a 6 year old cartilage piercing, so I am not sure how well these would do in a fresh piercing.

I got 20 of each bent barbell (eyebrow), 20 labrets, 20 horse shoes, 10 belly button, and 10 industrial. The industrial and belly button are the only earrings not 16G, they are 14G. Each were an assortment of colors!!

All of the earrings came in tact, no cracks can be seen in any of the balls/cones...but honestly, if one breaks on me...I have 79 more to choose from!!

Great purchase. I won't be needing new ones for a very long time.

Needed to include earrings with shipment. 2015-08-15 US 23708884 R3OCB87TNCFIF2 B00KVLMLTG 853604037 Hypoallergenic Sterling Silver Tiny Sun Stud Earrings for Kids (Nickel Free) Jewelry 4 0 0 N Y Very Detailed Wish they had been just a touch bigger but otherwise beautiful. 2015-08-15 US 33107350 RLO2AWOALL79X B00LEC4Y9Q 149125585 King Will BASIC 8mm Tungsten Matte Finish Brush Center High Polish Wedding Band Ring Comfort Fit Jewelry 5 0 1 N N Will you marry me? I know that's sort of sudden given that we just met, but...well...this ring is awesome, and sometimes I feel silly wearing it around without actually being married.

But I still do. Seriously, this is one fantastic looking and comfortable ring. Looking at the pictures here, and then after unboxing it (and these do come in a nice presentation box), I wasn't sure if I'd really like the matte finish on the center region. It seemed kind of boring. Yeah, I was totally wrong. Completely, utterly wrong. I love it.

I feel like I'd just babble about this ring, so I'll try to simply convey that it is very comfortable and looks (IMO) even better in person once you have it on. King Will makes several similar styles, and I've tried three of them: this one, [[ASIN:B010N8ATBS one with a stepped edge]], and [[ASIN:B010N89158 one with flatter polished strips around the matte finish]]. I like all three of them, but I'd say this one is my favorite.

As you likely already well know, tungsten carbide is not the same as pure tungsten. However, it is also much less expensive and has a lot of similar qualities - which is one reason why it is so popular for rings these days. What makes these rings so strong can also make them brittle, so rather than deforming like a gold band would if you hit it hard enough, these can crack. That's just a note, as you definitely don't have to baby these things.

Pros:
(*) Looks exactly like the product image, so if you like the pictures you should like the look of the ring in person (or, if you're like me, you'll like it more in person)
(*) Comfortable with smooth surfaces everywhere

Cons:
(*) Might cause your eyes to burn when you, albeit innocently, startle someone by spontaneously proposing in the line at Chipotle...and they break out the pepper spray. The silver lining, though, is that there will be tortillas all around to mop up and enjoy that spicy goodness

column6: Beone®Fashion Summer Bohemia Turquoise Silver Plated Bib Collar Necklace Earrings Jewelry Set
column13: Substantial and elegant treated turquoise set -- the lady loved it!
column14:
My lovely lady loves to wear jewelry, and what's not to love? The shine, the sparkle, the glitz -- it also makes gift-giving very easy, knowing that if it glitters, she'll probably love it. She never takes it off, except when it comes to the beach or the pool, and then she only does it reluctantly and tells me the whole time how naked she feels because she doesn't have her necklaces on. When I saw this, I thought this was a perfect glittery budget-friendly alternative to wearing her good stuff when we're enjoying the chemical-filled pool and the abrasive sandy ocean. If it gets lost or ruined, no big deal, and she still can have the security of her shiny necklaces.

It arrived on a necklace card and wrapped in plastic so that it wouldn't be damaged in transit. The treated turquoise is really beautiful. It's a substantial piece that looks elegant (not tacky, thankfully). The earrings perfectly match the necklace. When I gave them to her, she loved it (especially that it's teal, her favourite colour, and she thought I was ridiculously romantic for the gesture). She put them on right away and they have endured most of our summer adventures. The only drawback is when she wears them for extended periods of time, the necklace leaves some discolouration. Overall, we're both happy with what we got and I've been called The Best Boyfriend, so I win too!

I received this at a discount in exchange for a genuine critique.

column6: Parma77 Fashion Light Green Jade Queen Bangle Bracelet Christmas Gift
column14:
I love bangle bracelets so of course I was happy to try this -- I don't have anything quite like it in my collection just yet.

This is quite well-made. It is carved from one piece of stone and the surface is smooth with no flaws. As it is made from a natural material, there is some variation in surface color, although the overwhelming majority of the bracelet was precisely what you see on the screen. This does not appear to have been dyed in any way.

I have quite small hands and ordered a medium. I was able to get it on, but it was a close thing. Because this is a rather thick, natural material, there is no "give" the way there would be with say, a metal bangle. So my advice would be to order a larger bracelet than you think you need.

This has the weight you'd expect from jade and it warms to your body temperature the way you'd expect. Although I am not a gemologist, I have worked with beads made from some of the materials commonly used to simulate jade (dyed quartz, green serpentine, etc.), and those have a different look and feel to them. So as far as I can tell, this is genuine.

This is now one of the nicest items in my collection of work jewelry, and I think it could be used on a more formal occasion as well, especially if paired with pieces containing yellow gold or freshwater pearls.

Product provided by the seller for evaluation purposes.

column13: Really pretty ..great deal.. topaz is lighter than pics show..opal has a bright fire ..has filigree detail you can't see in pics
column14:
The topaz is far lighter than I expected. .it's actually even lighter than what showed up in my picture I think ! HA ! But I guess a flash can do that.
What I love and I hope you can kind of see in my picture... is that there is a beautiful deep filigree design all along the side.

I only really took off a star because the topaz is far lighter very much making it apparent that this is costume jewelry and then the opal has far too much fire..again pushing towards the costume end of things ...but as a whole I still really like to love the piece

If you like the picture I included, then you will love the ring ... really for the price it's wonderful .. the filigree detail surprised me and the seller really should have included a side view showing it.

Overall...if you know what you are getting into ..I would recommend it for a great sterling silver classy costume piece

column13: Very very cheap  product, mine came broken, wouldn't recommend it to anybody
column14: I bought this product and it came in the mail quick enough although I had to pay expedited shipping.  However I received it broken.  On the left and right side of the stainless steel engraving are two black leather bands which wrap through the engraving and then the two ends are supposed to be inserted in a circular cuff where the chain is connected to.  One of the black bands just hangs loose and you can see that it was supposed to be just cheaply glued in there.  I didn't wear my band for about a week or so and then put it on to go camping and when I came back my mom pointed out that it was broken and asked me if it was that was how it came.  It is how it came, I just hadn't noticed that both sides weren't the same.  I received a broken product from them and will update this review when I hear back from them.  I just filed a refund request so I will update to let others know how they treat their customers.

Rhodium :
Rhodium is the hardest of all the precious metals, it provides the most where resistance finish possible for the most demanding environments.
It provides a bright attractive finish that is non- tarnishing.

The Cubic Zirconia is exquisite, shines, and glisses, in any kind of light.

column13: Classic and comfortable, but scratches easily
column14: Beautiful, simple, elegant, shiny, and comfortable. The metal is highly polished, and becomes a band of pure shine when it catches the light. The rounded interior is very comfortable. It took a day for me to get used to the feeling of it on my finger (as I don't normally wear rings) but after a week of nonstop wear, I even wear it to sleep. The only reason I gave four stars was because the surface does scratch rather easily. I work in an office where the ring occasionally hits other metal surfaces, and I now notice tiny scratches all over it. However, they don't detract from the overall look of the ring, and I will continue wearing it for a long time. Very pleased with the quality and price.

column13: ... Aiyaya 4 carat cubic zirconia engagement ring is absolutely beautiful. I purchased a size 6 and it's true ...
column14:
The Aiyaya 4 carat cubic zirconia engagement ring is absolutely beautiful. I purchased a size 6 and it's true to size. The cubic zirconia just has an amazing shine to it when the light hits it. If you are looking for a ring that makes a statement this ring will do the trick. The rings comes in a very cute little red pouch. I love the flowered band that gives it such an elegant touch.
This is would be a perfect temporary set for anyone who is pregnant and is looking for a wedding ring to wear while their fingers are swollen. You definitely can't go wrong with the price.
I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for a honest and unbiased review.

column6: 1.25 Carat (ctw) Sterling Silver Princess & Round Black Diamond Bridal 3 Stone Engagement Ring 1 1/4 CT
column13: Returned for full refund.  (Review and pics included.)
column14:
5* for design in pictures.
4* band
1* stones
3* customer service

I returned it. I didn't want to but I was disappointed, even at the sale price of 179$ prime.

In the pictures, this ring looks absolutely perfect. In person, it looks very pretty at first glance and the band is nice - thick and sturdy but still feminine, even on the palm side of the hand. I've been sized multiple times at a size 7. The size 7 that I purchased was a pinch large for my ring finger but would have been worth re-sizing if it weren't for the stones.

In the pictures, the stones look symmetrical and even. The center stone looks larger than the side stones and the side stones look like they're equal in size and shape. In person, the center stone is still larger but one side stone looked twice as thick as the other side stone. And the cut... I wasn't expecting super fancy for the price, but I did expect that the basic cuts would at least be even. For the most part, the top facets looked fine but each of the side ones and angled ones looked completely uneven and when you looked at the three stones from one side (no matter what angle), they were not rectangles, they weren't parallel at all - messy, lazy cuts no matter how you looked at it, and just did not flow at all with the beautifully, smooth and sleek band.

My decision to return basically boiled down to value for the price as well as how it made me feel when I looked at it because really, it is about how you feel when you look at it, no? I have seen cheap ten dollar rings with perfectly even cuts - not that I want to buy a ten dollar quality ring, but that I could probably find a quality silver band with some black, basic cut synthetic stones that are evenly cut for less than this band and I'd feel better about wearing it, looking at it, and not minding other people seeing it. While I know not everyone is going to notice the unevenness of the stone sizes and cuts, I do. I have to look at it every day.

On the flip side, I have seen that most other reviews are from people that have purchased this as a gift or as an engagement ring. Had this been the case for me and I did not know the cost nor foot the bill, I would be far less critical as I would be grateful for the gift. Still, the blatantly uneven stones would still probably nag at me to some degree even if I did keep silent. I realise that this may be a personal issue/preference and some of you may not care or notice. All I know is that I'm not totally OCD, not even close, and this bothers me enough to mention for others out there who are.

The return was quick and hassle-free as it was a Prime purchase. Customer service for the company was quick to write me to ask for additional info as to why I was not satisfied so I wrote basically what I wrote here but also included some additional image links for clarification as to what was so disappointing about the cuts. I also stated, that I'd buy the ring again as I love the design if I could be guaranteed that I would receive a ring with stones that looked like the one in the picture (even with regard to cut). Or, I would even be willing to buy a more expensive version of the same ring if the band was white gold or platinum versus silver as the design is exactly what I've been looking for. I am pretty sure it's been well over a month now since I sent my reply to the company's question and never heard from them about whether or not alternatives are available.

As a side note: never brought the ring to a jeweler to have it appraised so I cannot speak for its authenticity. Although both the stones and the band appeared to be solid, the band did not have any stamp on the inside of the ring confirming it's silver.

I purchased this ring on May 6, 2015. I waited over a week to give considerable thought to the ring before I decided to return it and I do not regret the return. This original review is on Aug 15, 2015. I tend to wait to do reviews for at least a couple of months, if not longer, to ensure a quality overall review versus initial thoughts only with no follow up as those are the reviews I seek when deciding on whether or not to buy a product.w is on Aug 15, 2015. column6: Christian Mens Stainless Steel Abstinence 1 Timothy 6:6-16 \Man Of God: Pursue Righteousness, Godliness, Faith, Love, Perseverance And Gentleness. Man Of God: Fight The Good Fight Of The Faith In Christ Jesus\" Chastity Industrial Band Ring for Boys - Guys Purity Ring - Comfort Fit Ring"
column14:
I love this ring because it has 2 verses on it. Unfortunately there's a minor typo in the reference and it actually says 1Tim 6:16-16. I got it for myself though as a constant reminder of what's in those verses and that is printed correctly. Very comfortable fit once u get the right size...I went through 2 because the first was too big and size 10 is comfortable. A ring sizer came with my school ring and this is the right size (my school ring is also a size 10 from a jeweler and fits the same way). It does seem a little thicker than gold but not bad if u don't wear other rings on the same hand. It might catch on things if not sized right. It does fit comfortably but is noticeable because it's thick.

Oh, at work we have an XRF material analysis X-Ray machine that verified that this is 316 stainless steel which is the high grade of stainless steel. They may have messed up the scripture reference, but this is a good quality steel that should last years and a very comfortable ring :)

column14: Very pretty ring.  It is very shiny and it sparkles from all directions, especially when there is brighter light around.  It has a heavy, weighted feel to it.  It was not too uncomfortable to wear, although it feels wider on my finger than the majority of my other rings.  It also seemed to be a bit bigger and I had to reorder a smaller ring so it was not so wide and so it did not rotate around easily from the weight of it.  I recently purchased two other rings for the same finger, so I am sure the size of my finger has not changed.  It did not look too "fake."  The stone has a clarity to it that made it look close to my diamond wedding set (to the natural eye anyway) and the silver was not gaudy looking at all.  Great ring for the price, especially since I normally do not like round cut diamonds at all.  Perhaps the halo look adds to my attraction to this ring.

column6: Sterling Silver Simulated Diamond Twisted Eternity Ring (Size 5 - 9)
column14:
[[VIDEOID:adabe0a0f158811831eadb9925815db5]]This review is for the Sterling Silver Simulated Diamond Twisted Eternity Ring.

This is a beautiful, twisted silver ring with high quality simulated diamonds. The twist is very feminine and works its way around the band. The diamonds are just the right amount. It is not COMPLETELY blingy but just the right amount of sparkle.

The inside of the ring have specks of open windows to allow sparkle with the diamond flecks. The twist design is smooth on the inside so it feels good against my skin. It is very comfortable but designed well to look very elegant and classy.

The ring comes in a nice hard box with velvet ring setting. It can be wrapped for gifting. This is a great value ring for the amount of silver you get. Everyone will love this ring! 5/5 stars for design, elegance and value.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: La Sportiva Boulder X Shoe - Women's
column14:
The Boulder X was my second choice for an approach shoe. I initially bought 5.10 Guide Tennies, but the first pair was too big and when I went down a half size they were too small. So I jumped brands. I ordered both the Boulder X and the Mix (also La Sportiva). I was really impressed with the fit of both shoes (having European half sizes basically gives them American quarter sizes). The heel was snug and I had no slippage (something lacking in the 5.10s). The Boulder X has a lace around the heel that really snugs things up.

My overall impression of the Boulder X was that it was rugged. It has a nice looking edging zone at the front of the toe. The lugs were nobby and looked like they would be good for hiking. There is a lot of lacing, which is both good and bad since they are a pain to get on and off but there is a lot of customization to fitting. The rubber seemed pretty sticky, picking up plenty of dog hair as I tested them out around the house. They definitely look and feel more like a hiking shoe than a climbing shoe. They are a lot stiffer and have a lot more support than a climbing shoe or more minimalist approach shoe. Just testing them out in the house I noticed they were quite warm

While I liked the Boulder X I did end up sending them back in favor of the Mix. The Mix is much lighter and more flexible. The rubber seemed softer and stickier. The trade off is in support and durability. I feel like the Boulder would probably last longer and perform better on longer hikes. But currently most of our approaches are less than an hour, so I opted for the more comfortable of the two shoes. But if I find myself doing longer approaches the Boulder X is top on my list.

column14: I put these on the minute they arrived on my doorstep and ran out the door for a 6 mile run. I could tell almost immediately that I would enjoy running in these shoes. As the run wore on the shoe nearly disappeared into the background, exactly what I look for in a good running shoe. I look forward to many more miles with these on my feet. The only thing even slightly negative I have to say about these shoes is in regards to heel striking. IF you are a heel striker these shoes could be awkward. The M strike plate positioned slightly in front of the heel makes getting from your heel to toe off difficult, or at least not as smooth as one would like. A great shoe to work on your foot striking in though!

column13: Great Shoes once you ditch the crappy laces and get all white cotton laces!
column14:
Comfortable compared to other brands that do the same styles (Polo Ralph Lauren, Tommy Hilfiger, Lacoste, Penguin).
I ended up buying two pairs because I like the look of these and the wear really well with tapered and skinny slim jeans.

A bonus I found is that they are easy to clean and the white canvas and rubber rand doesn't get dirty as easily as one would think.

My only gripe is these Avery Dash III come with the worst shoe laces ever. They are like a waxed nylon fabric, really long, thin and in a dirty white shade beige color that do not match the look and color of the shoes. I ended up getting all white cotton laces from a local shoe store and they look sharp.

I'm also not sure why these are still selling for over $60 online when most local shops sell these between $20 and $40 on sale.

I'm actually looking for the leather versions of these right now so I can have something for the North East Fall/Winter wardrobe.

column6: Shoe GOO Adhesive
column13: the stuff is not easy to work with
column14: One sole came loose on the most comfy pair of shoes I own: a Converse court shoe no longer available. I was a few days from going off on a 3-week vacation, and it was either break in a new pair of tennies or fix the old ones. The reviews of Shoe GOO, though a bit mixed, convinced me to give it a try. I was skeptical at first: the stuff is not easy to work with, and I wasn't sure I'd gotten it applied well enough. Kept the shoe clamped more than 24 hours, and when I tried it out, the sole looked to be solidly attached. Not only did the fix make it through 3-weeks in sunny Italy during which I averaged about 10,000 steps a day, but the shoe is still solid after another month of routine daily wear.

column13: Excellent shoe, cant say enough about them
column14: I bought a pair of the Rovers around the first of December, 2014 for work.  I wear a fitbit constantly and I average approximately 4 miles a day walking at work.  (split approximately half and half inside and outside)  Up and down stairs and ladders, and a lot of time on knees with the toe of one shoe or the other on the ground.  I figure for about 8 1/2 months, at 5 days a week, I've literally put about 680 miles on them.  There is still nothing wrong with them, although they're beginning to show a little age.  No threads broken, nothing has come loose, and they still have the original laces in them.  The sole on them looks nearly as good as the first time I put them on. Although i'm not a hiker, or outdoorsman, I see no reason these would not do a fine job for trails or whatever.  If and when they ever wear out, i'll absolutely have to have another pair just like them, and perhaps another pair in a different color for wearing with casual attire.

column6: Asolo Men's Drifter GV Hiking Boot
column13: I don't think there is a better boot available for me.
column14:
I would highly recommend ignoring the negative reviews on this particular boot. Also use a bit of common sense and thinking outside of the box...something we humans tend to ignore.....Bad apples happen. This can be applied to life in general...For instance, the growing hatred of Police Officers in our country....Bad apples....every single group of people in existence have bad apples...every single business, group, club or organization has bad apples. The human race in its entirety....bad apples everywhere....If you apply this common sense logic to life...it...well it will be beneficial.

4 years of service, and I still can't wrap my mind around how perfect these boots are. If they made a non-goretex version I would also buy those, but I can honestly say, I NEVER think about my feet while wearing these. I don't get overly hot in them, and I trust my life to these boots. The fit is unreal, the lacing system is a tank, and the heel lock is incredible. I have a mostly flat foot...basically extremely low arched feet, and it is a dream to wear these. The design and build of this boot is ridiculous. They are also extremely lightweight in my opinion. Comfort is outstanding. The stiff sole is great...and I can run in these easily when I need to..Tread is perfect for anything I've done and anywhere I've been...wet or dry.. The tread doesn't wear overly fast, and that is great. Toe cap is phenomenal, could kick some teeth out if needed. On top of that, the looks are in my book, perfect.

It's one of those boots, that you might consider buying several pairs in the event you can't buy them years down the road...

I have tried pretty much all of them...you name it...The drifter wins across the board.

Hope this review helps coming from someone who exposes their boots to the most extreme environments and conditions.

column13: I stitched the foamy insole thing to the rubber from the inside trying to hold it in place (not easy as the shoe had to be turne
column14: The usual water shoe issues. You can buy their equivalent at walmart and have the same outcome. Of course they work and last as just as long. I cannot remember what I paid for these but if it was more than $7 I definitely paid too much. The rubber probably cost more than the shoes were actually worth. The soles slide out. After a month or so of use, the bottom rubber started separating itself from the sock part. I stitched the foamy insole thing to the rubber from the inside trying to hold it in place (not easy as the shoe had to be turned inside out). After repeatedly stabbing myself in the finger with a leatherworking needle (normal sewing needles hate going through rubber) too many times, I reassessed the situation and came to the conclusion that the foamy insole was just going to tear anyways, so I stopped. My handiwork lasted about a week. The drawstring is great. These will be tossed after this summer in lieu of something better for next year.

column6: Clarks Men's Meningreysuits Fisherman Sandal
column13: Nice, but initially narrow and has weak sole
column14:
I usually wear a size 12 in almost all shoes and sandals and since my feet are on the wide side, I usually order W whenever available.
But there was no WIDE option with these sandals, so I ordered 12 - and this is how it went:

LOOKS: good design, quality, material - just like in the photos.

FIT: My feet got it, but it was very narrow in a painful way, and it took long time (as in several weeks) to stretch and accommodate my foot. So if you have wide feet, you have be patient for a few weeks until it breaks in. If you have regular/narrow feet, then you're okay with this point.

SOLE: initially it was fantastic. The cushioning was amazing. However, it got compressed quickly and lost its elasticity. So after a few weeks, it was just an average OK sole just like any other unknown brand.

DURABILITY: the upper is just fine. A few threads flying here and there, but no biggie. The problem is with the sole, which is made of soft/weak rubber. It just wears out so quickly (in addition to losing its elasticity and compress-ability as mentioned before). This wearing out of the sole made it look less than what you'd like to wear in a decent outing. So I ended up wearing this for grocery shopping or for running errands on my own.

If these sandals had a different kind of sole, I would've bought many more. Everything else is just fine or perfect.

column14: I really like them now, but the shoes weren't very comfortable at first till I did a little surgery on them. Then I inserted thin airsole cushions cut to the shoe size and I inserted those in the shoes and tried that on for size. Works perfect for me. If later I buy another pair of hush puppies, I'll know exactly what to do so I can have a great fitting pair of shoes. I should explain that I have always had a hard time finding the right shoes to fit my feet.. Some shoes I have to send back for a refund. column6: Cocoons Fitovers Polarized Sunglasses Wide Line (ML)
column13: I like the Flex-2Fit temples- they can be adjusted to make ...
column14:
I bought these because I wanted a pair of sunglasses that would fit over my prescription glasses but not make me look dorky. I bought these instead of clip-on sunglasses because I mow lawns for a grounds company, and was hoping that these glasses would keep stuff out of my eyes and from scratching my prescription glasses. They do, mostly. because of the shape of the frame of the Cocoons and the shape of my face, I occasionally (about 5 times a day) get some flying grass/rocks/trimmer line between the lower right and left corner of the Cocoons and my face. Not a big deal, because before I bought these, I used an old pair of glasses (different prescription, thus poorer vision) that was scratched and pitted. Now, I can wear my daily glasses, and don't worry about scratching them up. In addition, these make trimming along bright white objects (concrete driveways, white siding, etc.) much easier, as I am not squinting. I like the Flex-2Fit temples- they can be adjusted to make the fit tighter or looser. I usually straighten the temples and bend them in toward my headThey are also great for driving as they cut the sun's glare, etc.
Overall, these were a great investment. I hope they last. Just beware, these may not fit snugly against the front of your face like some sunglasses would.

column6: New Balance Men's MT910V2 Trail Shoe
column13: I still have my original pair (worn out but good for the beach) and would have re-purchased the v1s ...
column14: Update 2:  Actually the 14 4E were slight too big - I got some blisters because of them being loose. I 14 2E would be a better fit for the 13 $E. What interesting is that the shoe fitting tool says they'd both fit *perfectly*.   Buying shoes online is still hard. ---   Update: Amazon has introduced a new way to see if 1 pair of shoes compares against another pair.  So I entered that I had the MT910v1s and wore them in 13 4E and they fit perfectly and Amazon recommended (with a fancy 3d graphic) that the V2 size would be 14 4e.  Well I took a chance and ordered a pair and guess what -- they fit perfectly. Amazon gets a GOOD JOB from me.  New Balance gets a SHAME ON YOU for wildly mis-sizing the V2 or these shoes.  -------------  I was thrilled hearing that New Balance was making an updated version of the 910s, I still have my original pair (worn out but good for the beach) and would have re-purchased the v1s again if they were available.  The bad news about the v2's is that the toe box area seemed significantly smaller and my big toe and the toe next to it hit the edge of shoe while walking, making it a very uncomfortable shoe.  I experienced the same issue with there 1069s and it caused me to have x-rays done to determine if I had broken a toe  (I didn't.)  I returned them without trying a larger size because they stop offering .5 increments at 13 4E.  I hope new Balance starts sizing their shoes correctly. I'd expect a v1 and v2 to offer the same toe box space.  I gave them 2 starts because the black and orange coloring looks really good.

column6: ECCO Men's Findlay Tie Oxford
column14:
I bought my first pair of Ecco Findlay's through Nordstrom, but I came here to buy another pair. I think the problem people are having with this style being "too big" is that recent shoe fashion is for a longer silhouette and toe area. A year ago, I bought a pair of trendy shoes from another manufacturer, and they definitely seemed too long. At first, I was tripping over myself going up stairs. I think ecco is trying to be a bit more trendy, and branching out from their great ,but spectacularly ugly classics like the Trak hiking, or the BOM. Ecco shoppers aren't usually young fashionistas, but the fact is that this kind of simple, classic shoe is very much in fashion right now. I live in a hip west coast city, and I want to look "on point", but be able to walk all day. This is the shoe.
Finally, I have a very similar pair of eccos from 2012. They are incredibly comfortable. I was wearing them almost every day for three years, and there is NO sign of wear on the soles or heels. They will go on for ever. The top leather is worn and stained, but that's because I often hike on rocky, wet trails wearing these oxfords! Ecco are fantastic shoes for anyone with foot problems.

column6: KEEN Utility Men's Detroit Mid Soft Toe Work Boot
column13: Ok, but KEEN needs to improve the soul.
column14:
Pros.....
-Very comfortable after a three week break in period. I can wear them for 8-10 hrs a day no prob(other than the squeaking)
-Quality seems unsurpassed upon
unboxing.
-Seem to be waterproof from the water I have had sprayed/splashed on them.

Cons.....
-These suckers squeak like no other!!! Sounds like I'm waking in plastic shoes all the time, which surprises me because the quality of materials seem to be excellent.
- maybe breathable, but my feet seem to get rather hot in them, but not wet. (I don't have real sweaty feet though)
- soul seems to be a little too soft. I have worn them every day for 8-10 hours a day outside, and they have some pretty good size chunks out of the soul like when you rip a pencil eraser,(see the picture by my thumb and finger) and all I've done is walk on concrete, street, and some occasional gravel/rocks. Don't see the soul lasting too long.
-price seems to be a bit high for the time period I foresee them lasting.

Overall I would prob buy another pair depending on how long these last. "If" I get a year out of them, they will prob be worth the money.( but what I see in three weeks with the soul, it'll be a push to make it a year I think). When I first inboxes them I thought they would last 5 years or so.

column13: Sometimes they are more comfortable than a pair of sneakers
column14: High quality shoes. I wear them almost daily. Sometimes they are more comfortable than a pair of sneakers. Inner sole is decent, but I replaced them with aftermarket ones. Not Gel inserts, which I think is more of a marketing success than real foot comfort. Inner soles don't need to be super soft - they need to be supportive. They look good with khaki work pants or with jeans. They get a little hot in the summer, but it's black leather, what can you expect? It's physics. I've got some complements on the looks and only on the longest days do my feet feel tired or ache. They can be a bit uncomfortable when climbing a steep incline, but they are not hiking boots.  They are good for walking around, standing on flat surfaces, and offer good support when standing on a ladder (which is a big reason to wear boots in my opinion). The soles squeak a little on some surfaces, (waxed linoleum) which is annoying and makes it difficult to sneak into work if you are running a couple of minutes late. They keep you honest.

column6: Montrail Enduro-Sole Unisex Trail Running Insert
column13: My goto insert for any serious athletic shoe
column14:
They have fantastic arch support that holds up and does not compress or sag over time and the heat molding makes them extremely comfortable. I have them in my running and trail shoes as does my wife.

To heat mold my second pair, I put a board over the toe portion of the insert to keep it flat because I do not like the feeling of having something holding my toes in the shoe.

The fit is true to size and I did not need to trim any of the inserts. My wife uses them in a women's size 9 Merrill hiking shoe and whatever running shoe she wears (too lazy to go look at the moment ;). I use them in my La Sportiva Bushido and New Balance 1080; both men's size 11.

I would love to see an option with just a bit more cushion under the ball of my foot, but these are easily the best inserts I have ever used.

column6: Scarpa Men's Kinesis Pro GTX Hiking Boots
column13: Number One Piece of Gear for Technical Trails
column14:
I bought a pair of these to replace my Fabiano's for a week of heavy packing on Isle Royale National Park. I put about 10 miles on them prior to the trip to break them in.

We got stranded on the island due to ferry trouble and ended up being there for eight days. We did about 50 miles on extremely technical trails with full packs (45 lbs, in my case).

On smooth rocks the size of a house, often tilted as much as a 45 degree angle that you had to walk along: flawless grip and good ankle support on the angle. Feet stayed put very well side-to-side, slight movement inside the boot when going down the rock face.

On trails FILLED with basketball-sized rocks that you had to walk on for miles, or solid roots for miles: flawless grip, not one slip until it rained, then less traction on the wet rocks, but not one turned ankle.

On stairstep inclines or very steep solid rock inclines: This is where the boot proved to be the perfect Isle Royale piece of gear. The toe of the boots grabbed the rock tightly and the stiffness of the sole made it easy, safe, and comfortable to push hard as you climbed.

On the few level, dirt trails: seemed to be a bit heavy and stiff-soled.

No blisters, though by day eight, I started to have some of my big-toe callouses get hot.

The fit is great for my size 41.5, standard-shaped feet.

The materials and workmanship are the highest quality.

The only downside is that the weight and the stiffness of the sole/ankle support make them a bit too much for daily hikes or where the terrain is civilized. These are big, heavy boots, ideal for technical trails with a heavy pack where you can't afford any kind of injury. Today, they fit like slippers and I wear them for all my packing.

column6: Sole Thin Sport Custom Footbed
column13: The instructions recommend putting these in the oven (I know
column14: I have very flat feet - so flat that it's hard to slip a piece of paper under the arches!  I was introduced to these full length sport supports at a local sporting goods store a few years back, and was very impressed by the firmness yet flexible insoles.  The instructions recommend putting these in the oven (I know, right?!) at a low temp for 10 min, then once out of the oven, for you to place your feet onto the insoles so they will conform to the exact match of each foot. I did this once to try it out, but have since just put them out of the package into my athletic shoes (Saucony, Asics) and even my Converse, which if you wear them, know there is absolutely no arch support in any of them.  It does take s little while to get used to them as they are stiffer than the gel/foam inserts but I no longer get achy arches/feet.  And yes, pricey but for my foot health, worth it...plus Amazon offers it at a better price than specialized shoe stores.  I also wear Birkenstocks on my non gym/sneaker days.  Very happy!

column13: How long do you expect a pair of $50.00 shoes to last while working in a kitchen? Mine have lasted 20 months of near daily use!
column14: First of all, let me preface this review by saying, I am a Chef in a commercial kitchen and these shoes slip-resistant sole works well in a wet an oily environment. I purchased them in December of 2013 and they have been worn 6 days a week every week since. They were a bit tight and stiff at first (bought a 12R) but were broken in in no time at all. They have served me well and they are about $10.00 cheaper now than when I first purchased them.They are advertised as having leather uppers; if that is so, then there is a very thin veneer of leather over something else. Having said that, I need to replace them because the shoe uppers are now cracked and peeling and allow my feet to get wet. Not a pleasant experience...blisters tend to develop in a wet environment, even if I powder my feet. If you are not in a wet and greasy environment all day, these shoes will definitely do what you need them to do! Even if you work in a damp/greasy kitchen, you can't go wrong for $40.00.

column6: Birkenstock Women's Mayari Sandal
column14:
I have always heard great things about Birkenstocks, and while I don't necessarily find the Arizona style to be ugly, they aren't very "me." However, after working in retail for the past couple of years, as well as walking around campus in some less-than-supportive shoes, I have started to develop plantar fasciitis and I knew I needed some sandals that would actually benefit my foot, since my summer shoe selection is pretty pitiful. These are perfect! The antique lace color is really nice (it's kind of like a slightly shimmery off-white color) and the style is more feminine than I thought which is a plus, and after the break in period when the shoe has completely molded to your foot (which for me was only a couple days of wearing them a bit, and no blisters or anything like that), they have become one of the most comfortable pairs of shoes I've ever worn. I'll be sad when the weather gets cold and I can't wear them anymore!

They definitely run a bit big, I'm a very true size 9 and the 39 fits me really well. As far as the width, I got them in a regular because that's the only width I could find anything in. My feet are on the narrower side of medium and while I think a narrow size would be a bit better, the regular width lets my feet spread out and I don't find it uncomfortable at all. These don't seem to run quite as wide as some of the other styles I've seen.

column6: KEEN Rockbrook CNX Shoe (Toddler/Little Kid/Big Kid)
column14:
I bought these for my daughter before we went on a 10 day vacation to a cabin the mountains. She absolutely loves them!

*SIZE: They fit really well. I'm learning that there is a huge range within sizes for toddler shoes. For example, her foot measurement indicates a size 8 and she has shoes that are sizes 7,8, and 9. Some of her 8s probably won't fit for another year. These shoes were true to size!

*TRACTION: They have great traction for hiking, playing in the dirt, or running in circles.

*BREATHABILITY: They are breathable so her feet aren't enclosed and sweaty.

*VERSATILITY: They're great for playing in the water...walking through a river, riding in a boat or on a jet ski, etc., and quickly switch to great shoes on land.

*COLOR:The color isn't great, but it's neutral so it doesn't attract a lot of attention.

GREAT PURCHASE!

column6: Keds Women's Champion Original Canvas Sneaker
column13: Where did your sole go, Keds?
column14:
I'm so sad! Over the years I've loved Keds. First I loved them from afar and would buy the wannabe off-brands from Payless and Target when the real thing was too expensive. When I finally brought myself to pay up for a pair of true lime green Keds a decade or so ago, I wore them for years until no wash could resurrect them from their new grayish-pistachio color, and even then, holes in the canvas were the first decayâ€”a tolerable decay. I love the style with everything, they come in my hard-to-find wide size, and, most importantly, they lasted.

But this time, like others have reported, the rubber outer around the sole started pulling away within a month tops. I probably do more walking than most people, but when I got my previous pair of Champions a couple years ago, this wasn't a problem, and I was walking and wearing them more than I am now. Back then, the sole wore down smooth and just thinned out over time. This pair, though, the sides are pulling away from the insole, the whole bottom sole is popping out from the bottom, and I could flip the rubber outer up and put my finger between the two. They're actually falling apart. They're exploding unwearably. There's no point to spending this much money on the real thing anymore when the off-brands last at least as long.

I'm pretty bummed out. I've really tried to make this last an excusable lifespan with some shoe glue, but I shouldn't have to do that after just a couple months.

The eyelets were at different heights from side to side and the inner lining was loosely stitched into the boots which caused wrinkles which in turn caused a very uncomfortable boot when laced up.  These boots cost WAY TO MUCH to get this in return.. I could have gone to Wallmart if I wanted cheaply made boots. At least they would have kept replacing crappy boots until there was satisfaction. column6: KEEN Women's Harvest MJ Button Shoe
column13: Order at least a full size smaller than normal!
column14:
These shoes run at least a full size too large. (I put on my thickest socks and they were still huge.) I'm used to Keen's variance and was trying to be careful (I have Keens that range from 6.5 to 7.5 that fit the same) but was still surprised at these.

If we leave aside the problem of sizing, they're cute and comfortable, although they feel cheaper compared to other Keens I own (and I own a lot of Keens); they are vegan (which isn't ordinarily an issue; I don't want to think about how many cute fabric vegan Keen shoes I have in my closet...it's a lot) but they feel flimsier than the standard Harvest Mary Jane style. Whether the fact the sole is softer and more flexible is an advantage or not is a matter of personal preference.

Although this doesn't impact my rating, given the third-party seller's return policy, returning them will cost about 1/3 of the price of the shoes themselves--so I'm going to be waiting for my daughter to catch up in a year or two and keep my fingers crossed she still thinks they're "So cute, Mom!" then. (And buyer/returner beware of the return policy of onlineshoes.com.)

column6: Rothco 8'' GI Type Jungle Boot
column14:
I've worn Jungle boots for 40 years (not the same pair). These are a little flimsy compared to issue boots. They quit putting in a lot of tread in the center of the boot so they are thin in the center where the steel shank is supposed to be.

To make these usable,
1. Put on 72 inch laces so you can let the seam in or out as needed without unlacing the boot each time you take it on or off.
2. Put in some jell soles in them and on top of the jell soles a standard insert or arch support.
3. Cover the leather in oil or saddle soap so that the leather becomes flexible.
4. BREAK THEM IN by wearing them awhile each day until they conform to your feet.
Overall they cut some corners in building these, but for the price they work ok.

column13: Excellent Shoe for a Toddler/Small Youth
column14:
I have a very petite 7 year old who still wears a size 10/11 toddler shoe. It is so hard to find properly fitting, well made and durable soccer cleats for a child of her size. I spent quite a few hours browsing online trying to hunt down shoes that 1. Came in her specific size, and 2. Were from a reliable brand so that I knew they would hold up.

* These shoes easily slip on over soccer socks, with a dip low enough under ankles that they do not rub against shin guards.
* Once laced, these shoes have zero issues staying tied.

We have used the same pair of cleats for 2 soccer seasons now and they have held up well without falling apart, scuffing terribly or having the cleats rub and wear down. I will happily buy the next size up in this brand for my daughter once she grows.

column14:
I purchased the 54mm Wayfarers because I feel I have a larger face. I also typically need larger sunglasses. I returned a pair or 52mm aviators in the past in exchange for 57mm pair. So, I thought the 54mm size Wayfarers would be right for me. Well, 54mm is big! They are right on the cusp of being too big for me. I kind of wish I went with the 50mm. So, if you are thinking about the 54mm, be sure you really have a larger face or just truly prefer a larger frame because these are big in my opinion.

I should have gone to a store to try them on first. Everything else is great. Quality is superb. I wore many pairs of Oakley in my younger years. These Ray Bans feel just as good or better in terms of precision and quality. Metal frame inside the plastic, high quality lenses, hinges super strong, solid coloring rather than paint.

column14:
Good affordable lifting shoes. Had a pair of Reebok Power Lifts but someone stole them from my desk at work. I bought these as a cheaper replacement and just keep them in my gym bag to prevent them from being stolen. The toe box on these shoes is fairly wide so they feel like clown shoes. The high tops keep my heel in the back of the shoe where it's supposed to be but also allows flex in the ankle. The shoe provides a flat platform to squat and deadlift in and prevents your body weight from being shifted forward. Shoe has some breathability so foot sweat isn't that big of an issue when lifting but I also haven't used these for any sort of gym classes.

I'd recommend them as a good starting point for folks looking for lifting shoes.

column13: Perfect as a small cross-body purse! Great value for the money
column14: I needed a new small black purse to replace my expensive Tignanello purse that broke. I wanted a small cross body purse to hold my phone, credit cards & cash, car keys, cosmetics pouch, glasses case but  I didn't want to pay a lot like I had before. Spent the money but the strap broke anyway.  I usually don't write product reviews but after already buying and returning 3 purses before I found this one I felt I could help someone else save some time by letting them know this one was great. In fact it's perfect.  I really appreciate that it is roomy enough to hold everything I need while still being compact. It is leather and isn't smelly like some of the other purses I read about.  The only improvement I would make is to add internal slots for credit cards so there is no need to carry a small wallet but I know that some people - when changing purses - prefer to not have a built-in credit card and money section. With this purse I have separate pockets for phone, for keys, for money/credit cards so I always know where things are without having to go into the main body of the purse. The adjustable strap loses the "folds" after one use. The workmanship looks good. Great value for the money! I recommend this.

column6: Propet Men's M3850 Washable Moc Walking Shoe
column13: Propet Needs to go a Couple Steps  ;-)  Further to Make This Shoe Great.
column14: This review is on behalf of my husband who has severe edema related to type 2 diabetes. His legs and feet are very large and mis-shapen and finding socks and shoes to fit and which look good is quite a challenge. We have purchased this type of shoe before and know that the entrance to the slip on is very narrow. No matter how wide the shoe we order the entrance doesn't correspond with the width. We did purchase shoe stretchers and shoe stretching spray to help alleviate that problem but somehow shoe and sock manufacturers don't seem to understand the trials of finding nice looking footwear for severe edema related problems. We have spent hundreds of dollars in this search and when we find something that works the manufacturer stops production and the search is on for something else. If I could go to a company, sit down with quality control and design something that makes buyers gasp in wonderment it would make my day. I recently purchased three pair of these shoes in various colors and hope that Propet continues to manufacture these shoes but with a WIDER entrance for the foot to slip in. My husband hates the clunky looking diabetic shoes on the market that come with a Velcro closure. He wants a classy looking comfortable shoe and I don't blame him. Now, if we can just find him great socks to fit his feet and legs.

I returned them, only to discover after further reading that a wide toe box is good in a minimalist shoe. It allows for a natural splaying of the toes. I ordered a smaller size anyway and my toes banged against the end of the shoe. I returned them for being too small. I would have bought another pair, but realized another shoe, with a bit of padding, would be better for me for running longer distances. I went with Carson Footwear. However, if I ever have a wad of extra cash laying around, I would buy these again for everyday wearing and short runs.

column14:

The only issue I'm starting to see is the durability of the sole. While the foam-like sole is comfortable and absorbs adequate amounts of shock, it has begun to start peeling. Bits of yellow have started to flake off whether from running on a trail (and I'm assuming grinding on rocks or wood) or walking around and occasionally dragging my feet.

However for the value and comfort it is definitely minor flaw and I would definitely consider buying another pair.

column14: I ordered this Baggallini for a trip to Europe. It arrived the day before I left and my first thought was that it would be too small. column6: Foster Grant Wes Men's Rectangular Multifocus Glasses
column13: FRAMES ARE JUNK LENS ARE GOOD
column14:
For me these glasses are great however the frames are very poor construction. I ordered my first pair incorrectly with a low prescription thinking that was the starting point and it would progressively increase. Returned them for a 2nd pair which i wore for a few weeks,
That pair was also returned in a bag with the right temple broken off and nose piece pin snapped. Damage occurred with a small drop from breast pocket to hard floor.
Amazon promptly shipped 3rd pair which I now have received. The same temple was loose compared to right side at the hinge right out of the box.
So these I am trying to keep these protected and not put them in their case or carry them around.

Amazon has been great with the return and replacement. I agree with some customers who complain they can;t find the return area on the website . That was tricky for me as well. But is an option in your cart or when your on the product selection page. It may nto appear if you had not ordered the part so I 'm not sure if that's what made it difficult.

I would stay away from these glasses if your needing to carry them around with you to many places.
But they are worth a shot if you need bifocals or more. You may need to return them however i suspect this risk is no worse with any other web order business and Amazon has an easy method for returns.

column6: Lucky Brand Medine Leather Conv Messenger Backpack
column13: Lovely color, quality leather, and very well made
column14:
I love teal and was eyeing this bag for a long time before I decided to go for it. It is a very nice bag, and I'm glad I did.

I was wondering about the actual dimensions of this bag, so here you go: 11.5" x 10.5" x 3" at the top and 4.5" at the bottom. That's measuring seam to seam, since the bag can take different dimensions when full, of course. (Actually, the width is 11" at the top and 11.5" further down.)

I was hoping to be able to carry 8.5"x11" things in here, and that will work. You can't carry 11" things in the back pocket, though, because of the way it's tacked down.

Pros:
1. Perfect deep teal color.
2. Heavy, high-quality leather
3. Loads of pockets to help keep things organized: back outside, narrow side pocket, front inside (just under the flap), and then the main compartment has a zipper pocket on one side and two open stash pockets on the other side.
4. Adjustable-length shoulder strap, and the nifty conversion to backpack

Cons:
1. I was hoping to be able to carry 8.5"x11" things in here, and that will work. But I wish they'd made this just a smidge wider.
2. You can't carry 11" things in the back pocket, though, because of the way it's tacked down.

Other:
1. I couldn't tell online, but the buckle on the front is for show and conceals a magnetic clasp underneath. Similarly, the back pocket is not entirely open and has a small magnetic clasp
2. I also had no idea from looking online that there's a sunglasses pocket on the side of the bag. This has a somewhat awkward closure with a strip of leather that slides under a loop (no real fastener). I probably would have preferred this to just be open, without that awkward closure.

I was fortunate enough to get this bag at a discount from its current price on Amazon, so I'm feeling pretty lucky about that. If you find this bag from another seller online, it's about $100 more than Amazon's currently selling it for. (Yeah, the tag on the bag itself says $188, and Amazon's current price is $88.)

Among the things I most love about this bag is that I can expect to have it for years because it's such nice leather and so well made.about $100 more than Amazon's currently selling it for. (Yeah, the tag on the bag itself says $188, and Amazon's current price is $88.)
